{"name": "Bestial Creature", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/abilities/paw-print-tan.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are considered both Humanoid and Beast when it comes to rules affecting creatures types.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "A69S7OIOQPX7A5GA", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Beseech Providence", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/people/cleric-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are no stranger to setting an example of your faith, both in your deeds and in your words. You have advantage on Presence (Persuasion) checks made to implore someone to carry out a selfless act that is at most inconvenient to them (such as helping a neighbor rebuild their shed or donating a small amount to a starving creature).</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Devotee", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "CZKRUMYCK6X1L5WN", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Choose Your Battles", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/people/infantry-army.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>The supreme art of war is to subdue the enemy without fighting. You have advantage on Presence (Intimidation) checks made to convince others to back down from a fight with you.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Militant", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "QJK4VRMK8IZWD41C", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Connected", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Any time you enter a city or town and have spent at least a day there, you know how to get in contact with those who deal in shady business, and how to get a friendly introduction.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Scoundrel", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "QECKCO8JGKG5L6Z9", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Eye for Quality", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/trades/textiles-cloth-dye-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are skilled at appraising any non-magical object that could be crafted by a trade you are proficient with. You have advantage on checks to determine the base price of these crafts and identify forgeries. You also learn whether the object you are appraising is magical, but not what its effects are.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Artisan", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "5Z5KEPS9RQKUVCPC", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "A Helping Hand", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/wave-halt-stop.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>The first time you ask for an object or help from someone whom you have helped before, they are heavily inclined to oblige. In the situation where a Presence (Persuasion) check is required, you have advantage on the check.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Humanitarian", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "XRDOHUHF3RTLV18F", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Institutional Sway", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/treasure/brooch-crown-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your insignia and general air distinguish you from the unwashed masses, making bureaucrats and authority figures less likely to dismiss your concerns. Should you need to arrange an audience or appointment, you have advantage on Presence (Persuasion) checks to do so.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Aristocrat", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "2BWN854LL0WQ39J3", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Know the Ropes", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/settlement/ship.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are no stranger to the workings of a ship. You can easily negotiate passage on a ship for you and your companions in exchange for labor during the voyage, provided the ship has enough excess capacity to accommodate you. Should the crew require convincing, you have advantage on the associated Presence (Persuasion) checks.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Sailor", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "6S8K0D2XXAKPWE4J", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Lay of the Land", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/wilderness/tree-oak.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are familiar with traveling the land and fending for yourself.  When traveling in the wilderness you can easily find food and water for yourself and a handful of other people.  As well, you get advantage on Intelligence (Nature) checks to determine whether a plant is edible and safe to consume, and whether water is safe to drink.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Outsider", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "U8KK1AON39A2OHR2", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Prepared", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-writing-brown-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Should you spend your next short or long rest studying an object, creature, or event, you gain advantage on the next Intelligence or Wisdom based roll you make, excluding Wisdom (Instinct), to understand something about the subject.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "background", "subtype": ""}, "requirements": "Early Scholar", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": "Background Features", "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "CEDNUQ4BN37WPXPH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Number of Chaos", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/clover-luck-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain a new Eikonic Number which serves as your <strong>Eikonic Number of Chaos</strong> (see the &ldquo;Eikonic Numbers&rdquo; Cleric Starter Ability for details).</p><p>You also gain access to the following <strong>Mantras</strong>, which can only be assigned to your <strong>Eikonic Number of Chaos</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>Chaotic:</strong> You can immediately either:</li><ul><li>Cause a small object to move a few feet.</li><li>Cause a small fragile object to crack or shatter.</li><li>Swap places with a creature up to 10ft away.</li></ul><li><strong>Control of Chaos:</strong> You can re-roll 1 die before the end of your next turn, and must take the new result.</li><li><strong>Embrace the Chaos:</strong> A creature of your choice that you can see takes 1d10 chaos damage. You take half of the damage dealt, unless you spend a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith} Die to negate the damage against yourself.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "7RQ8BN29ZKQKDDPV", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Flux Mindset", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/clover-luck-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you take a rest, roll on the <em>Flux Proficiency Table</em>.&nbsp; Based on the result, you gain proficiency in that skill until your next long rest, after your new proficiency has been decided by this ability.&nbsp; Re-roll on the table if you land on any proficiency you already possess.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Flux Proficiency Table</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>1d20</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Proficiency</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1</p></td><td><p>Athletics</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2</p></td><td><p>Acrobatics</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3</p></td><td><p>Stealth</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>Sleight of Hand</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5</p></td><td><p>Arcana</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>6</p></td><td><p>Craft</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>7</p></td><td><p>Culture</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>8</p></td><td><p>Investigation</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>9</p></td><td><p>Nature</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>10</p></td><td><p>Insight</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>11</p></td><td><p>Instinct</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>12</p></td><td><p>Medicine</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>13</p></td><td><p>Perception</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>14</p></td><td><p>Theology</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>15</p></td><td><p>Deception</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>16</p></td><td><p>Intimidation</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>Perform</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>Persuasion</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>Pick a Tool Proficiency</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>Pick any Skill or Tool Proficiency</p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "K7N259JP8I363OMC", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Invitation of Chaos", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/clover-luck-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Once per rest, when you succeed on a check, you can choose to fail it instead to gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die. </p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "95LFWCUJ0S9AQ254", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Rule of All", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/diplomacy-unity-alliance.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Once per long rest, as a reaction, you can send out a burst of unseen chaotic energy at a creature you can see within 60 feet. That creature is struck by a brief confusion that undercuts their composure; mental rhythms stumble, words or orders are flubbed, movements are shaky, and complex actions are misordered, causing the intended Lair or Legendary Action to fail.  In addition, that creature cannot use either until the start of its next turn.  <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon reaching the Growth Level at 11th overall level, you can regain usage of Rule of All by taking a Short Rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Chaos Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "BSNHEGZSSX19MKJ5", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Mantra: Sheer Chaos", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/gaming/dice-pair-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you learn this ability, you learn the Mantra <em>Sheer Chaos</em> associated with your <strong>Chaos Number</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>Sheer Chaos: </strong>Roll on the 1d100 <em>Sheer Chaos Table</em>, this effect activates at the beginning of your next turn.&nbsp; You can feel this effect building, know what it will be, and can warn your allies.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>While any of your Sheer Chaos effects are active or set to activate on your next turn, you cannot roll again on the <em>Sheer Chaos Table</em>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Sheer Chaos Table</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td style=\"min-width: 44px;\"><p><strong><em>#</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>Effect</em></strong></p></td><td style=\"min-width: 44px;\"><p><strong><em>#</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>Effect</em></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>1</strong></p></td><td><p>Lose all @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Dice.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>44</strong></p></td><td><p>You are able to speak with animals and understand their speech for 1 minute.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>2</strong></p></td><td><p>You are <strong>silenced</strong> until you end your turn.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>45</strong></p></td><td><p>You have the <em>Force of Will</em> spell active for 1 minute without concentration.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>3</strong></p></td><td><p>On heads, you are <strong>sickened</strong> until you end your turn.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>46</strong></p></td><td><p>You are teleported to a location you can see within 100 feet.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>4-8</strong></p></td><td><p>Roll a 1d6 on the table below and pick one of the options from that.&nbsp; All creatures within 50 feet gain vulnerability to the chosen damage type for 1 minute.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ol><li>Pick: Bludgeoning, Piercing, or Slashing</li><li>Pick: Acid or Poison</li><li>Pick: Chaos or Psychic</li><li>Pick: Cold or Fire</li><li>Pick: Lightning or Force</li><li>Pick: Necrotic or Radiant</li></ol><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>47-49</strong></p></td><td><p>You summon a creature of a CR of half your overall level or lower decided by the GM.&nbsp; It has its own free will, and gains an Intelligence of at least 10 and the ability to speak your language if it lacked these before.&nbsp; While confused by its new locale, the creature initially regards you as an ally and will generally listen to your commands so long as you prove yourself an ally to it.&nbsp; It remains summoned until its hit points reach zero or a separate creature is summoned by Sheer Chaos.&nbsp; This creature&rsquo;s summoning does not prevent you from rolling again on the Sheer Chaos table.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>9-10</strong></p></td><td><p>You are transformed into a Toad as if transformed by the <em>Verminize</em> spell until the end of your next turn.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>50</strong></p></td><td><p>You gain true sight for 1 minute.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>11</strong></p></td><td><p>You are <strong>stunned </strong>until the start of your next turn.</p><p>Gain two @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Dice.</p></td><td><p><strong>51-52</strong></p></td><td><p>Restore all @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Dice.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>12-13</strong></p></td><td><p>Flip a coin.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>On heads, you grow 1 size and your physical attacks are one die size larger.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>On tails, you shrink 1 size, your physical attacks are one die size smaller, and you gain 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Either way, it lasts until the end of your next turn.</p></td><td><p><strong>53-56</strong></p></td><td><p>Pick an object or creature within 60 feet.&nbsp; You suddenly know one detail, secret, or part of its history, as decided by the GM.&nbsp; These facts are presented as if rolling highly on an Intelligence (Culture) check or divining some long-hidden past about the object.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>14</strong></p></td><td><p>You and all adjacent creatures start <strong>bleeding</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>57</strong></p></td><td><p>You gain the effects of the <strong>Quicken</strong> spell.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>15</strong></p></td><td><p>For the next minute, when you target a creature with a spell, heal all adjacent creatures by 1d6 hp.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>58</strong></p></td><td><p>Gain an additional action on your next turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>16-17</strong></p></td><td><p>You become spiritually linked with the first creature you see for 1 minute.&nbsp; You are both <strong>charmed</strong> by each other, and when either of you take damage, the other takes the same amount of damage.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>59</strong></p></td><td><p>Gain an additional minor action on your next turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>18-20</strong></p></td><td><p>You explode in Chaotic energy, taking 1d4 Chaos damage per Cleric level you have taken, and dealing 1d6 damage per Cleric level to all creatures within 10 feet.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die for each injured ally.</p></td><td><p><strong>60-61</strong></p></td><td><p>You briefly grow surreal ever-changing limbs out of your back that are difficult to describe, and gain a Fly and Swim speed of 100ft until the end of your next turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>21-22</strong></p></td><td><p>An Incept is summoned adjacent to your position.&nbsp; It is hostile to you.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>62</strong></p></td><td><p>Gain an additional reaction on your next turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>23-24</strong></p></td><td><p>Cast <em>Lash Out</em>.&nbsp; Treat yourself as a target for the spell as well.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>63-64</strong></p></td><td><p>You appear identical to another creature of your choice that you have met.&nbsp; This is an illusion that instantly is recognizable as an illusion when someone or something attempts to touch the illusive parts.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>25</strong></p></td><td><p>You are <strong>blinded </strong>until the end of your turn.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>65-67</strong></p></td><td><p>A surreal swirling of energy encapsulates you.&nbsp; You are resistant to all damage types until the start of your next turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>26</strong></p></td><td><p>You are <strong>deafened </strong>until the start of your next turn.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>68</strong></p></td><td><p>Pick a creature within 60 feet, they must roll a DC 13 Presence (Save) check or else become <strong>stunned</strong> until the end of their next turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>27-28</strong></p></td><td><p>The nearest creature to you must make a DC 10 Presence (Save) check.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>On success, nothing happens.</p><p>On failure, you and the nearest creature swap bodies for 1 minute.&nbsp; During this time, your mental attributes remain the same, and whichever of you is a Chaos Cleric gains 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>69-71</strong></p></td><td><p>A duplicate of yourself appears next to you for 1 minute.&nbsp; You and your duplicate are the same person in two bodies, and share all mental faculties, stats, and a turn.&nbsp; Each self can take their own action each turn, but all other actions are shared, movement is split between each self, and your health and mana pool is shared and unchanged.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>29-30</strong></p></td><td><p>If you die within the next 1 minute, your body will be reborn as if affected by the <em>Reincarnate</em> spell 1d4 days later, regardless of whether or not you are alive at that time.&nbsp; When this happens, restore all your @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Dice.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td><td><p><strong>72-74</strong></p></td><td><p>You can feel your body jitter and jerk, crackling with energy, as if your mana has a mind of its own.&nbsp; All damage you deal becomes Chaos damage until the end of your next turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>31</strong></p></td><td><p>Strange music radiates from you for 1 minute, being audible up to 100 feet away.&nbsp; If your GM is playing music, they must change the song to another song for all to hear.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>75-77</strong></p></td><td><p>The ground around you shifts and twists strangely in a radius of 30 feet, becoming difficult terrain.&nbsp; All other creatures in this radius must make a DC 15 Strength (Save) or Dexterity (Save) check or be Restrained.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>32-33</strong></p></td><td><p>All creatures within 60 feet see strange scintillating shapes that cover parts of their vision, giving disadvantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks and a -5 to Awareness for 1 minute.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>78-80</strong></p></td><td><p>You have +5 AC until the end of your next turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>34-35</strong></p></td><td><p>Flip a coin.</p><p>On heads, you are <strong>frightened</strong> of the largest creature within 60ft until the start of your next turn.</p><p>On tails, you are <strong>frightened</strong> of the smallest creature within 60ft until the start of your next turn.</p><p>Either way, gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>81-85</strong></p></td><td><p>Pick a non-living object nearby that is not being worn or held.&nbsp; It becomes entrapped in chaos, jerking and twisting wildly, and dealing 1d20 chaos damage when touched for the next 1 minute.&nbsp; At the end of this duration, it appears as if nothing had happened to it.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>36</strong></p></td><td><p>You are <strong>deafened </strong>until the start of your next turn.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>86-87</strong></p></td><td><p>Pick a creature within 60 feet, they must roll a DC 15 Presence (Save) check or else become transformed into a Toad as if by the <em>Verminize</em> spell until the end of their next turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>37</strong></p></td><td><p>You have -2 AC until the end of your next turn.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>88</strong></p></td><td><p>You gain the effects of the <strong>Haste</strong> spell.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>38</strong></p></td><td><p>You are <strong>petrified </strong>until the start of your next turn.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>89-90</strong></p></td><td><p>The effects of the <em>Cloak</em> spell are applied to 3 creatures of your choice within 30 feet.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>39</strong></p></td><td><p>You are overwhelmed by vertigo and fall <strong>prone</strong>.</p><p>Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</p></td><td><p><strong>91-94</strong></p></td><td><p>Spells cost half mana until the end of your next turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>40</strong></p></td><td><p>You or an adjacent creature of your choice regains 5 hit points at the start of their turn for the next 1 minute.</p></td><td><p><strong>95</strong></p></td><td><p>All creatures within 30 feet must make a DC 15 Presence (Save) check or else become <strong>charmed</strong> by you.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>41</strong></p></td><td><p>All your melee attacks and touch spells inexplicably have a 60ft range for 1 minute.</p></td><td><p><strong>96-98</strong></p></td><td><p>Your form changes as if the spell <em>Mutate</em> was cast on yourself.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>42</strong></p></td><td><p>Become ill-defined and strange in shape, as you take on the essence of another being.&nbsp; For the next 1 minute, when asked to roll a skill check, you can choose any of your skills to make that skill check in.&nbsp; However, you cannot use the same skill twice within the duration.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td><td><p><strong>99</strong></p></td><td><p>The first Critical Failure you roll, if rolled in the next 1 minute, counts as a Critical Success instead.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>43</strong></p></td><td><p>The area is filled with extremely thick smoke in a radius of 30ft around you.&nbsp; For the duration, anyone within is <strong>blinded</strong> and cannot be seen, and anyone without cannot see creatures within.</p></td><td><p><strong>100</strong></p></td><td><p>A golden apple appears in your hand.&nbsp; Taking a bite from it causes the rest of the apple to disappear, and the creature to roll on this table.&nbsp; Its taste constantly changes in the mouth.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Chaos Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "JFWE7N4P0B68717F", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Chaos Dominion Spells", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/clover-luck-white-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Clerics of the Chaos Dominion learn the following spells when able to cast Cleric spells of the same spell level.&nbsp; These spells are always prepared and don&rsquo;t count against your prepared spell amount.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Dominion spells are considered Cleric spells when learned this way.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Chaos Dominion Spells</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Able to Cast</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Spells</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1st Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.7N5KBCOM40ZX65EO]{Arcane Arrows}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.PZLUQ36LJVGLMZ4R]{Lash Out}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2nd Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.A0XHQ6VS7PDGN9FJ]{Cloak}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.FZ8CHP8N6M0PGLI1]{Discombobulate}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3rd Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-3.VROEDKWBUZ57MFV7]{Rolling Thunder}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-3.TA1E58P8XATOBEQH]{Virulent Outbreak}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4th Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-4.YL8USCAX1ZTDKOA1]{Shapeshift}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-4.7H0M1UB9Z1ZVHSJ0]{Remove Arms}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5th Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-5.LAT1CHJ5SCDL566O]{Reincarnate}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-5.RS1WH90WHNO7H1AR]{Kinetic Burst}</p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "V475LKBO4K3Z04IA", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Synchronization of Chaos", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/hypnosis-mesmerism-watch.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You can spend @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice in the following ways:</p><ul><li><strong>Synchronization of Chaos:</strong> When multiple creatures are rolling simultaneously for the same reason, including you, you can spend two @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice to replace another creature&rsquo;s roll result with one of your dice rolls.<br /> Alternatively, when you roll multiple dice at once, you can spend two @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice to change the result of one die to the result of another die you rolled.&nbsp; <br /> This change cannot trigger an Eikonic Number or Miracle for any creature involved.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Chaos Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "17NZ5JIJ6XJZ18VM", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Thrives in Chaos", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Requirement: </em>The Miracle Adept ability</p><p>Once per long rest, when you skip your turn from taking a Desperate Action in the previous round, trigger a Miracle.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Chaos Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "CW7SV7WCSEMZYMHK", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Blade Arms", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/claws/claw-insect-grey.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have two pairs of arms, with the 2nd set located beneath the first.  The forearms of your upper limbs are a pair of sharp chitin blades.  These limbs are considered natural weapons equivalent to shortswords.  You are proficient with these blades, and can use them as if dual-wielding.  <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You do not gain extra attacks, actions or minor actions with these limbs.  Additionally, while wearing any armor, shields only grant bonuses when held in 2 hands due to limited mobility.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "BX78MZPVZ495PPDG", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Death Sting", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/biological/stinger-insect-grey.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have a stinger on your abdomen that is bred to kill. If you attempt to sting a creature with it, make a melee weapon attack with proficiency. On hit, the target takes 1d10 piercing damage, and you take 1d10 chaos damage as the stinger rips out. On a critical hit, the target becomes @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.SRRBLPRSJWGUR551]{Poisoned}. Otherwise the target must make a Constitution (Save) Check of DC 10 + your proficiency bonus. On failure, the creature takes 1d6 poison damage and is @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9X088PM7H5U2S1HQ]{Sickened} until the end of your next turn. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You cannot use this racial trait again until you take a <em>Long Rest Action</em> to focus your body on regrowing the stinger.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "W2JOTIASQTIRW3IA", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Extra Arms", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/claws/claw-insect-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have two pairs of arms, with the 2nd set located beneath the first.  You can choose either set of arms to complete actions with, can carry or hold things in up to all four hands, can carry up to 2 two-handed objects, and can reload up to 2 loading weapons at once without penalty.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;However, you do not gain extra attacks, actions, or minor actions with these limbs.  If you hold more than two shields, you only gain the Armor Class bonuses of the first two, as more than two becomes unwieldy and unhelpful.  Additionally, while wearing any armor, shields only grant bonuses when held in 2 hands due to limited mobility.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "5QYD3QFDLZO2NKCD", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Flutter Fall", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/biological/wing-insect-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>While conscious, you flutter your wings to prevent yourself from taking falling damage.  This does not apply while wearing heavy armor.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "XQVA2ZE3HFJHJ8Z4", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Flutter Jump", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/biological/wing-insect-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your fluttering wings add a +10ft to your vertical and horizontal jump distance.  This distance is halved while wearing heavy armor.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "3RN1CJEJ8YBYOC14", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Handsy", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/claws/claw-insect-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Whenever you make a Strength (Athletics) check to grapple a creature of equal or smaller size using all four arms, then you gain advantage.  Once you succeed at grappling a target this way, you cannot gain this benefit again for the next hour.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "ND986T2ORMSDKFYJ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Lifter", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/claws/claw-insect-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You count as one size larger when determining your carrying capacity and the weight you can push, drag, or lift.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "4F8FWF6AU6ZW5AWV", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Multitasker", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/claws/claw-insect-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>With your extra hands, you can work with your hands more efficiently than others. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When taking a <em>Long Rest Action</em> to work a trade based on using your hands, you can additionally take a <em>Rest Action</em>, getting more done in less time. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, for each hour spent working with your hands, you complete 1.5 hours of work. For example, an 8 hour task can be completed in 6 hours instead.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "DSW72S4UGRPZ789H", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Natural Armor", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/claws/claw-insect-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your chitin exoskeleton is comparably tough.  While not wearing armor, your Armor Class is 11 + your Dexterity Modifier.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "2S9EWQFOXT06P29E", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Olfactory Antennae", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/claws/claw-insect-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Scout chk'tu have highly specialized antennae built for foraging.  By smell alone, they are able to locate and identify flowers and other notably scented flora at up to 100ft away.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "PX53DTW4FKMESH8I", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Royal Piping", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/tools/instruments/megaphone.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As a minor action, you can let loose a loud piping or horn noise like a howl that radiates up to 120ft.  All sleeping creatures that hear it are awoken, and up to 5 allied creatures of your choice that hear it gain temporary hit points equal to 5 or your level, whichever is higher.  Temporary hit points gained this way can be stacked.  You can use this racial ability once per long or short rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "6LMVQ9ZOP41IHVCP", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Acts of Faith", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/holy/prayer-hands-glowing-yellow-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You can spend @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice in the following ways.&nbsp; If an ability does not specify a specific amount of @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice, then you can spend up to as many @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice as you have available:</p><ul><li><strong>Divine Cure:</strong> As part of healing a creature, spend your @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice to increase the hit points recovered.&nbsp; Alternatively, touch a creature and spend your @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice to heal it directly as an Action.</li><li><strong>Divine Deflection:</strong> As a Reaction, you can spend @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice to decrease the attack roll of any creature within 30 feet.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Divine Karma:</strong> As a Reaction, before you know the result of the roll, you can spend 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Die to decrease the number rolled on any (Save) check done by any creature within 15 feet.&nbsp; This cannot be stacked.</li><li><strong>Divine Protection:</strong> As a Reaction, spend your @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice to increase the number rolled on any (Save) check done by any creature within 15 feet.&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Divine Smite:</strong> As part of an attack action or spell attack that deals damage, you can spend @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice to increase the damage of the attack.&nbsp; If you roll an Eikonic Number as part of the attack roll, deal 5 additional Radiant damage.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Cleric", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "JE4KI8AHSZRG8WHH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Clerical Approach", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/books/book-tooled-blue-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>The world is filled with countless religious and magical denominations and forms of belief.&nbsp; This information is no secret to a cleric, and often their interactions with such differing forms of belief or magic can affect their magics themselves.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>The following is a list of viewpoints on contradictory beliefs.&nbsp; When you take this ability, choose one of the following forms of belief, as well as the trait with it.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>To change your character&rsquo;s form of belief, you must reach a philosophical breakthrough as a <em>Long Rest Action</em>.&nbsp; When you do, you lose access to the trait of your previous Clerical Approach, and may choose another one.&nbsp; This process is mentally taxing, and you cannot make the change again until 1 month after choosing a Clerical Approach.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Exclusivism&nbsp;</strong></p><p>Exclusivist clerics are those that believe that there is only one &ldquo;correct&rdquo; truth or form of belief, and that the beliefs of others are counterfeits or corruptions of the truth.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Trait</em>: When you prepare spells for the day, you can prepare 2 extra spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>When damaged by a spell that you have prepared from your cleric spell list, you can spend your reaction to halve the spell&rsquo;s damage to yourself.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Inclusivism</strong></p><p>Inclusivists believe that all forms of faith or belief point to a singular truth, encouraged by similarities and downplaying differences between different faiths.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Trait</em>: As an action, you can replicate onto yourself the effects of a concentration spell that you can see affecting another creature within 30ft of you.&nbsp; The effect only lasts until the start of your next turn.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>If the spell is of a higher spell level than you can cast, the initial action costs 2 Mana.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Pluralism</strong></p><p>Pluralists make little distinction between faiths. Each is valid to the particular cultures or groups that follow them.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Trait</em>: When a creature casts a non-concentration spell within 60ft of you, you can replicate the spell once within 1 minute of the spell happening at the Mana cost of 2 + the Mana cost of the spell.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>You cannot replicate 8th or 9th level spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Syncretism</strong></p><p>Syncretists carry a unique faith based on their personal life context, believing bits and pieces of numerous different beliefs that best fit their viewpoints and experiences.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Trait</em>: You learn 1 cantrip from any spell list.&nbsp; Additionally, for each spell level that you become able to cast or have been able to cast above 1st, add a non-Cleric spell to your Cleric spell list. These spells can be prepared and count as Cleric spells, and use Wisdom as their spellcasting ability.</p><p>You cannot gain access to non-Cleric spells of 8th or 9th level this way.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "novice"}, "requirements": "Must have the Cleric Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "RVBAX8AXLOK0TRYA", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Divine Inspiraiton", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/holy/yin-yang-balance-symbol.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have become well-versed in the mantras and ways of your beliefs.  Seldom are the moments when you are found at a loss for inspiration with your faith to guide you.</p><p>&nbsp;When you roll any of your @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.CTOHXD4403501WIK]{Eikonic Numbers}, you can immediately activate one of the following Mantras.</p><ul><li>Your Awareness and Wisdom (Perception) checks are increased by +5 until the end of your next turn.</li><li>Your AC increases by +1 until the end of your next turn.</li><li>You gain +1 on all save checks until the end of your next turn.</li><li>You can restore up to your Wisdom Modifier worth of temporary hit points distributed amongst creatures within 15 feet of you.</li><li>You have +1 on skill checks until the end of your next turn.</li><li>Any unassigned Mantra from the same Divine Dominion as the rolled Eikonic Number.</li></ul><p><br />&nbsp;Upon reaching the Growth Level at 11th overall level, you can activate this ability twice when you roll an Eikonic Number.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "novice"}, "requirements": "Must have the Cleric Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "8JTZPLSCYX3QARDO", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Eikonic Numbers", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/holy/prayer-hands-glowing-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Every Cleric has a mark or idea that symbolizes their faith; an Eikon. When you feel this faith manifest, you give your mantras life&mdash;either vocally or internally&mdash;channeling that belief into action.</p><p><strong>Eikonic Numbers and Mantras</strong></p><p><strong>Eikonic Numbers</strong> trigger assigned <strong>Mantra</strong> effects when rolled. Any time you are rolling dice and naturally roll one of your Eikonic Numbers on a die of any size, treating d100 rolls as a single die, you activate all Mantra effects associated with the rolled Eikonic Number. These effects stack, even if you roll your Eikonic Number more than once as part of a single roll. When you roll with Disadvantage, your Eikonic Number only triggers if it matches the lower of the two results.</p><p><strong>Gaining Eikonic Numbers and Mantras</strong></p><p>In general, when you gain an Eikonic Number, you must pick a number from 7 through 12 that isn&rsquo;t already one of your Eikonic Numbers.</p><p>Eikonic Numbers are categorized by potency: Lesser (7 or 8), Moderate (9 or 10), or Greater (11 or 12). Eikonic Number Potency determines how many <strong>Mantras</strong> can be assigned to it, and is based on how often that number gets rolled. Lower potency numbers are rolled more frequently (fewer dice can roll the higher potency numbers) but trigger fewer Mantras, while higher potencies are less frequent but trigger multiple Mantras simultaneously.</p><p>Mantras can only be assigned to their associated Eikonic Number, up to the number&rsquo;s <em>Mantra Limit</em> as defined by its Potency in table below. You can replace assigned mantras when you gain a level in Cleric or on a Growth level.</p><p>If you have multiple Cleric sub-classes, you can gain more Eikonic Numbers by choosing to take the &ldquo;Eikon&rdquo; ability from subsequent sub-classes.</p><p><em>Eikonic Number Potency Table</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Potency</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Available Eikonic Numbers</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Mantra Limit</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lesser</p></td><td><p>7 or 8</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Moderate</p></td><td><p>9 or 10</p></td><td><p>2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Greater</p></td><td><p>11 or 12</p></td><td><p>2, plus Faith Abides*</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>* When you roll a Greater Potency Eikonic Number, Faith Abides (from the Faith ability) also activates without having to replace a Mantra effect.</em></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Cleric", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "CTOHXD4403501WIK", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Faith", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/holy/prayer-hands-glowing-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>At their core, a Cleric is one whose faith gets them through tough situations.  A Cleric without faith is no Cleric at all.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;@Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice are <strong>1d6s</strong> that can be spent on various Cleric abilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You can retain up to 2 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice by default.&nbsp; That maximum increases for every odd-numbered Cleric level gained starting at Cleric level 3.&nbsp; For example, at Cleric level 8, you can hold a maximum of 5 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Die on a long rest. If you gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Die while at your maximum, roll the @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Die and gain temporary hit points equal to the result.&nbsp; If you lose a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Die while out of @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice, unless stated otherwise, your @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice goes into the negative.&nbsp; There is no negative cap to @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice.&nbsp; While you have negative amounts of @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice, you cannot use abilities that cost @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice, and you have Disadvantage on Wisdom (Save) and Wisdom (Theology) checks.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You cannot trigger your Eikonic Number, a Natural 1, or a Natural 20 via the spending of your @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, when you roll your Eikonic Number, you can replace one <strong>Mantra</strong> with the following effect:</p><ul><li><em>Faith Abides:</em> Gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Cleric", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "65D4NMYRBMKHW59K", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Miracle", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/holy/chalice-glowing-gold-water.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Roll doubles on your @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Dice</li><li>Roll doubles of any of your Eikonic Numbers on a d20 roll with advantage</li><li>Roll any of your Eikonic Numbers on a 1d100 roll</li></ul><p>Then you can choose to activate one of the following Miracle options:</p><ul><li><strong>Ex Tempore:</strong> Immediately cast a spell as a Non-Action.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li><strong>Deus Ex Machina:</strong> Before the end of your next turn, you can cast a Cleric spell of 1 spell level higher than the highest leveled spell that you know.</li><li><strong>Ex Nihilo: </strong>Before your next rest, the next spell you cast costs no Mana if it is of a spell level equal or lower than half your Proficiency Bonus.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Cleric", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "BREZS34CQ6PFBCNF", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Prayer", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/holy/prayer-hands-glowing-yellow-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>During a long rest, you can enter into a communion with your deity or complete a ritual core to your belief.&nbsp; When you do, roll a 1d100.&nbsp; Your result determines which divine effect you will receive until your next long rest or until 24 hours pass, whichever comes first.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>After seeing your result on the <em>Prayer Results Table</em>, you can choose to either increase or reduce the result at the cost of 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Die.&nbsp; Once you do,&nbsp; roll the @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Die and apply it to the result.&nbsp; If you spend a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Die on this, then if the result is less than 1 or greater than 97, change the result to a 1.&nbsp; You cannot spend more than 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Die per rest in this way.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Prayer Result Table</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td style=\"min-width:50px;\"><p><strong>Faith Roll Result</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Effect</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>01</p></td><td><p>You are filled with doubt.&nbsp; Your @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith} Dice are set to -1 and you cannot gain @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith} Dice.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>02-20</p></td><td><p>No response.&nbsp; No effect.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>21-40</p></td><td><p>Select one Cleric Mantra. You can activate that Mantra as a non-action once.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>41-42</p></td><td><p>Your awareness increases by +5.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>43-44</p></td><td><p>When you speak, all creatures understand what you are saying.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>45-46</p></td><td><p>You have advantage on Intelligence (Save), Wisdom (Save), and Presence (Save) checks.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>46-47</p></td><td><p>You can trigger a Cleric Miracle as a non-action once.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>48-51</p></td><td><p>You have a hover flying speed of 60 feet.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>52-53</p></td><td><p>You can see @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.YE63H7VLOHW7NFHO]{Invisible} creatures.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>54-57</p></td><td><p>You have advantage on one d20 roll of your choice.&nbsp; You can choose to apply this to a roll after seeing the result.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>58-62</p></td><td><p>Your AC increases by 1.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>63-69</p></td><td><p>You are immune to becoming @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9YPWLY1IHQV3MRLO]{Diseased}, @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.SRRBLPRSJWGUR551]{Poisoned} (including inebriation), @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9X088PM7H5U2S1HQ]{Sickened}, and @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed}.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>70-74</p></td><td><p>When you land an attack, you are healed by 1d4 Hit Points.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>75-77</p></td><td><p>You gain 5 times your proficiency bonus in temporary Hit Points.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>78-82</p></td><td><p>As an action, you can spend any number of your Hit Dice to heal creatures within touch.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>83-85</p></td><td><p>You can transform yourself into and out of any form option available for <strong>Shapeshift</strong> as a minor action.&nbsp; These forms all follow the rules of the Shapeshift spell, except they have a share Hit Point pool equal to double your overall level that is retained between transformations. When this pool of Hit Points falls to 0, you are transformed back, you subtract the maximum Hit Points of the form from your normal current Hit Points, and this Prayer Result is no longer.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>86-88</p></td><td><p>If a creature touches you or anything on your person, it regains 1d10 Hit Points and is cured of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9YPWLY1IHQV3MRLO]{Disease}.&nbsp; In addition, the creature must make a Wisdom (Save) check against your spell save DC or be @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed} by you for 1 minute.&nbsp; The creature repeats this save at the beginning of each turn until it passes and the charm is removed.&nbsp; Once a creature has been affected by this once, it cannot be affected again.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>89-90</p></td><td><p>Gain Immunity to one damage type or condition of your choice.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>91-92</p></td><td><p>You gain 1 point of Luck.&nbsp; This does not expire.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>93-94</p></td><td><p>You have 10 more Mana than your maximum. Gain 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith} Die, regardless of your maximum.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>95-96</p></td><td><p>If you die during the duration, you immediately come back to life with full Hit Points one time.&nbsp; If your body is completely destroyed by the attack, you are reborn in a new body as if the spell <strong>Resurrection</strong> was cast on you.&nbsp; Gain 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith} Die, regardless of your maximum.&nbsp; Once this happens, it cannot happen again for the next 24 hours.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>97-99</p></td><td><p>Your belief deepens.&nbsp; Roll twice more on this table and take both results.&nbsp; Reroll results of 01 and 97-99.&nbsp; Gain 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith} Die, regardless of your maximum.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>100</p></td><td><p>You have a profound spiritual experience.&nbsp; You can enter and exit a <strong>Divine Form</strong> as a minor action for the duration.&nbsp; This form retains your general shape and size, but can appear as anything to your liking, so long as it is both fitting to your Dominion and fittingly divine in appearance.&nbsp; All changes and additions are real during this time, but do not add to your capabilities.&nbsp; While in your Divine Form, you have an extra Action, Minor Action, and Reaction per turn, and can Levitate with a Fly Speed of 30ft.&nbsp; Gain 3 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith} Dice, regardless of your maximum.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "adept"}, "requirements": "6th level overall and 3rd level Cleric", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "ASZ0LJ8H48GD7DQ6", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Providence", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/nature/cornucopia-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When preparing spells as a part of a rest, you can select a creature nearby, one of your Eikonic Numbers, and one Mantra you know, so long as the Mantra can be associated with that Eikonic Number.  Until your next long rest, when that creature rolls the selected Eikonic Number, they gain the benefit of the selected Mantra and you gain 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.  Once per long rest, if they fall unconscious, you can activate a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.BREZS34CQ6PFBCNF]{Miracle}.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "adept"}, "requirements": "6th level overall and 3rd level Cleric", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "JWUZ8MK65EG4I4MB", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Self-Sacrifice", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/books/book-stack.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Should you take damage from <strong>Saving a Target</strong> as a desperate action, the following happens:</p><ul><li>You can spend 1 of your Rest Dice to restore your Hit Points.</li><li>You can spend 1 of your Rest Dice to restore the saved target&rsquo;s Hit Points.</li><li>Gain 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&amp;#x1F56F; Faith}&nbsp;Die.</li><li>If the saved target would have fallen <strong>unconscious </strong>before you intervened, you can make an opportunity attack against the attacker as a non-action.</li><li>If you fall <strong>unconscious</strong> from the attack, the saved target regains Hit Points up to half of the damage dealt to you.</li><li>If you are <strong>Killed Instantly</strong>, the protected creature learns one of your Mantras permanently assigned to the Eikonic Number that you had it assigned to. They know this Mantra so long as you are dead.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Must have a Cleric Adept Ability", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "9QL8V9MDFLPW6JTH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Spellcasting (Cleric)", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/rune-sigil-black-pink.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your connection to your deity has been rewarded with the miracle of spellcasting.  Despite your previous capabilities at spellcasting, you find yourself progressively more magically capable by channeling your natural Mana through your faith in your deity.</p><h4><strong>Cantrips</strong></h4><p>Upon gaining your 1st level of Cleric, you know three Cantrips from the Cleric's spell list.  You will learn additional cantrips as you advance in the Cleric class.  You gain an additional Cantrip when you hit Adept Cleric, and then another at Expert Cleric.</p><h4><strong>Preparing and Casting Spells</strong></h4><p>A Cleric, like all spellcasters, expends Mana to cast spells (expanded upon in the Mana section of Magic).&nbsp; As well, you regain your Mana fully on a long rest, and partially on a short rest.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Like other spellcasters, a Cleric can prepare and memorize a list of spells that they can cast each day.&nbsp; However, since Clerics lean upon their deities for their magic, they do not learn Cleric spells in the traditional sense.&nbsp; Instead, they become capable enough to channel more powerful spells.&nbsp; As such, Clerics can prepare a number of spells from the Cleric spell list that they are capable of casting equal to:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Your Cleric level + your Wisdom modifier, (minimum of 1)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>These are the spells that can be chosen from this day.&nbsp; For example, Thadius is a 5th level Cleric with a Wisdom of 17.&nbsp; He can prepare eight spells, picking a combination of spells from the 1st, 2nd, or 3rd level Cleric spell.&nbsp; Thadius can cast any spell he wants until he runs out of Mana, but he cannot cast a spell that he has not prepared.&nbsp; This means that if he has 2 Mana left, but has only prepared 3rd level spells, then the Mana will go unused until he regains Mana or prepares new spells.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;A Cleric can change the spells they have prepared at the end of any long rest they take.&nbsp; The act of preparing them does take time, though.&nbsp; It takes 1 minute per spell level for each spell on your list of prepared spells.</p><h4><strong>Spellcasting Ability</strong></h4><p>Being that you obtain your magic ability through intense devotion and faith, Wisdom is the spellcasting ability for a Cleric.  Meaning that your Wisdom modifier comes into play when setting the DC for your Cleric spells and when making an attack with one.</p><ul><li><i>Spell Save DC:</i> 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier</li><li><i>Spell Attack Modifier:</i> your proficiency bonus + your Wisdom modifier</li></ul><h4><strong>Ritual Casting</strong></h4><p>You can cast a Cleric spell as a ritual if that spell has the Ritual tag, and you have the spell prepared.</p><h4><strong>Holy Spellcasting Focus</strong></h4><p>You may use a holy focus, a specialized item used to channel and cast spells, as a spellcasting focus for casting your Cleric spells.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;While in the Cleric's possession, a spellcasting focus allows spells to be cast without most material components.  Material components that have a cost or are said to be used up by the spell cannot be replaced using an arcane focus.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Cleric", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "SWRVTEHG4DXWU4VK", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Cleric Spells", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-runed-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>1st level Clerics get access to Cleric Spells, which consists of 1st through 7th level spells.  However, you do not have access to all of them right away.  These spell levels become accessible as follows:</p><p><i>Cleric Spell Levels</i></p><table><tr><th>Spell Level</th><th>Unlock Requirements</th></tr><tr><td>Level 1 Spells</td><td>1st Level Cleric.</td></tr><tr><td>Level 2 Spells</td><td>2nd Level Cleric;<br>3rd Level Overall.</td></tr><tr><td>Level 3 Spells</td><td>3rd Level Cleric;<br>5th Level Overall<br>(At least 4 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 4 Spells</td><td>4th Level Cleric;<br>7th Level Overall<br>(At least 6 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 5 Spells</td><td>5th Level Cleric;<br>9th Level Overall<br>(At least 8 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 6 Spells</td><td>6th Level Cleric;<br>11th Level Overall<br>(At least 10 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 7 Spells</td><td>7th Level Cleric;<br>13th Level Overall<br>(At least 12 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Cleric", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "K1Q6UGY7O0CBB4KD", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Darkvision (30ft)", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/perception/eye-tendrils-web-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have superior vision in the dark, and can see in dim light within 30 feet of you as if it were in bright conditions, and can see in darkness as if it were dim conditions up to the same distance.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "K2R4176S4B99TO6R", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Darkvision (60ft)", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/perception/eye-tendrils-web-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have superior vision in the dark, and can see in dim light within 60 feet of you as if it were in bright conditions, and can see in darkness as if it were dim conditions up to the same distance.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "1F3VSNLQTVMYA4PE", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fey Ancestry", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/consumables/fruit/apple-red-tree-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have advantage on save checks against being @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed}, and magic can't put you to sleep.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "B6D7U0WZJRIXIX5O", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Lesser Fey Ancestry", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/consumables/fruit/apple-red-tree-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have advantage on save checks against magically being put to sleep.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "N3YTNUP9KU47ZSZV", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Magic Means Nothing", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/movement/figure-running-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>If you would be reduced to 0 hit points by a magical source, you can choose to instead be at 1.  This ability can only be used once per long rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "B5HHGGP9E3Z81TY8", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Navigator", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/tools/navigation/compass-brass-blue-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You always know the cardinal direction that you are facing.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "OXY335G1JVFPRA6V", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Road Less Traveled", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/wilderness/terrain-river-road-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You are unhindered by non-magical rough terrain.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "FLXLXLGUDQ22W74S", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Unstoppable", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/movement/figure-running-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have advantage on rolls against effects that would keep you from moving.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "LZ84NS4W5BKFFEI8", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Adrenaline", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/movement/trail-streak-zigzag-teal.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As a reaction, you gain 1d10 + your Fighter Level temporary Hit Points.  You cannot use this ability again until you finish a short or long rest.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You gain another usage of this ability at each Growth Level.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "novice"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "S8VA8DQKIDWB6127", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Extra Attack", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/strikes-sword-scimitar.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you make an attack action, you can make two attacks with your primary weapon instead of one.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "adept"}, "requirements": "6th level overall and 3rd level Fighter", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "SH5OCGLHHXV66GKI", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/people/infantry.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Through experimentation, practice, and maybe some help from a teacher, you have learned new forms of battle. Fighting Stances are methods of combat that grant the user pros and cons, but only while in use. Pick 2 Fighting Stances from the &ldquo;Stance List&rdquo; later in this section.</p><p><em>Usage:</em> Unless stated otherwise, you can change your Fighting Stance as a minor action or at the end of an attack action, so long as you are not @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.RK3DF56CKMQUV6DM]{Prone}. You remain in your current Fighting Stance until your weapon is dropped, sheathed, or otherwise removed from your possession, you become @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.RK3DF56CKMQUV6DM]{Prone}, @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.PEDR1J13VZXKUF3C]{Stunned}, or @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9KB959MRZ0H4IT4C]{Unconscious}, or until you end your stance as a minor action. <br /> If a stance requires a weapon with a certain trait, all weapons currently wielded must also have that trait, with the exception of shields and natural weapons. Unless the stance says otherwise, shields <em>can</em> be held in an available hand while in a fighting stance. Attacking with a natural weapon that does not meet the requirements of your current Fighting Stance causes you to end your stance before the attack.</p><p><em>Learning New Stances:</em> You learn 2 extra stances at each Growth Level.<br /> Many Fighter Sub-Classes have expanded Fighting Stance options. Once the unlock requirements for Fighting Stances from that Sub-Class have been met, you are able to choose Fighting Stances from that list when learning new stances as part of level up.</p><br><br><u><i>Stance List</i></u><br>@Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.AQKR36ORJ8UW7M7O]{Ammunition Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.U0YH0GDRUF7KZ3HP]{Boxing Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.59STQWZ34C00OVZP]{Finesse Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.4RWGBRI6CNCPMKCG]{Heavy Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.QEDI2ZY7AFB0GFXY]{Light Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.7ECXODBQJAZNTQFS]{Loading Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.TO8A2T5QL9GR8MAF]{One-Handed Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.98PGZKRSGDG2L2L7]{Quick-Draw Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.SK2FZU8XH2UZX0GP]{Ranged Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.H2554TR82JFKPYS2]{Reach Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.5TS3VRP8JKUPXU0Z]{Shield Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.4IQUGM1GK28XR39P]{Slugger Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.XK4PEQX6RYXIKTZ6]{Throwing Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.CAIFAC3V8NQRCZUQ]{Two-Handed Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.fighting-stances.OV4KEWGS7DFIDZ0Q]{Versatile Stance}", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Fighter", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "8O5S8E5F8E9ZQ5MP", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Size-Up", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/silhouette-grow-shrink-tan.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You can size up a living creature that you can see as a non-action.  When you do so, the GM tells you if the creature is closest to:<ul><li>1/4 Hit Points remaining.</li><li>1/2 Hit Points remaining.</li><li>3/4 Hit Points remaining.</li><li>Full Hit Points.</li><li>Or greater than full Hit Points.</li></ul></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Fighter", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "92GYIVKSFZIMYTB4", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Thrives Under Pressure", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/silhouette-hold-beam-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When using a Desperate Action, you gain the following boons:</p><ul><li>You have a +2 to all Save Checks until the beginning of your next turn.</li><li>You can move up to half your movement speed as part of your Desperate Action.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>You can swap heavy weapons as a non-action.</li><li>Your movement is unaffected by difficult or tight terrain.</li><li>You can choose to swap your Fighting Stance at the beginning of an attack instead of at the end.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "adept"}, "requirements": "6th level overall and 3rd level Fighter", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "ZBXFQL0LWH9PQUNJ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Weapon Fanatic", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/swords-triple-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Pick 3 weapons that you are not proficient in, you are now proficient in these weapons.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, you have advantage on all Intelligence (Culture) and Intelligence (Investigation) checks related to weapons or armors with which you are proficient, or Fighting Stances in which you know.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Must have a Fighter Adept Ability", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "57K1WUK53JJUHQ6N", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Weapon Savvy", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/strike-weapons-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">All fighters have their weapon of choice.&nbsp; While adventurers are generally proficient, you refused to stop at mere proficiency.&nbsp; Fighters who become savvy with a weapon gain bonuses that surpass proficiency and open new ways to wield that type of weapon.</span></p><ul><li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pick three weapons with which you are already proficient.&nbsp; You become Savvy with these weapons and gain the relevant effect from &ldquo;Savvy Effects&rdquo; below while you are wielding the weapon and the weapon is drawn.&nbsp; In addition, you gain a +1 to Attack Rolls with your Savvy weapons.</span></li><li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">You learn 1 additional savvy at each Growth Level.</span><strong><em><br /></em></strong></li></ul><p><br /><br /></p><p><strong><em>Savvy Effects: </em></strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">While using the weapon of choice that you are Savvy with, you gain the following benefits.</span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Savvy Effect Table</span></em></p><table><tbody><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><strong>Weapon</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Effect</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Blowgun or Throwing Star</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Silent Killer</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: When hidden, attacks with this weapon deal an additional 1d10 damage and the result of your previous Dexterity (Stealth) roll decreases by -2.&nbsp; This may reveal your location if your stealth becomes lower than a creature&rsquo;s Awareness.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Buckler or Shield</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Uncanny Block</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: When a creature that you can see hits you with an attack, you can use a desperate action to reduce the attack&rsquo;s damage against you by half.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shield, Tower</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Iron Wall:</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> When you make a Dexterity (Save) check to take half or full damage, you can use your desperate action to protect yourself.&nbsp; If you are holding your shield in two hands, then you can also protect one other creature within 5ft of you.&nbsp; Protected creatures take half damage when they would take full damage, and take no damage if they would take half damage.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Club, Greatclub, Hammer, or Knuckles</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Minor Concussion</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: When you land a critical hit, you can instead choose to do non-critical damage and the target makes a Constitution (Save) check of DC 14 + Strength Modifier, causing the target to be </span><strong>stunned</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> on failure until the end of its turn.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shortbow or Longbow</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Suppression:</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> As an action, you can expend 5 ammunition to suppress all targets within a 15ft cone until your next turn with a flurry of shots in the area.&nbsp; Suppressed targets get disadvantage on attack rolls while in the area, and if they move while under suppression then you can use your reaction to make an opportunity attack.&nbsp; Additionally, if you take a desperate action before your next turn then suppression ends.</span></p><br /><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Arrow Curving</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Your attack rolls are unaffected by half-cover, three-quarters cover, or the target being </span><strong>prone</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Light, Hand, Heavy, or Repeating Crossbow</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Stock Bash:</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> Your crossbow can be used as a 1d4 bludgeoning melee weapon as a minor action.  If you hit a target with this melee attack, you automatically Disengage and have advantage on attacking this same creature with your crossbow on this turn.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dagger</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Slit the Throat</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: You deal 1d10 extra damage to </span><strong>grappled</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, </span><strong>incapacitated</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">, or </span><strong>restrained</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> creatures.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Dart</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pinpoint</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Your proficiency bonus is doubled for attack rolls with this weapon.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Glaive or Lance</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Vault: </span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">As a minor action, you can plant and push off of your weapon to launch yourself higher, increasing your jump height or distance by +10ft.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><br /><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Riding Weapons</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Attacks against non-mounted creatures while on a mount have a +3 to hit, and deal an additional 1d6 force damage.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><br /><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Anti-Riding Weapons</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Attacks against mounted creatures are made at advantage.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Maul or Warhammer</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Ground Slam</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: In place of an attack, all creatures within 5ft of you must make a Dexterity (Save) check of DC 8 + your proficiency bonus + your Strength Modifier.&nbsp; On failure, the creature falls </span><strong>prone</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><br /><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Deconstruct</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Your attacks deal an additional 1d10 bludgeoning damage to constructs.&nbsp; Attacks do double damage to structures and stone objects.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hatchet, Battleaxe, or Greataxe</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Guillotine Strike</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Your attacks deal 1d12 extra damage to </span><strong>prone</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> creatures.&nbsp; If the attack kills a humanoid, it can behead the creature.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><br /><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Deforestation</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Your attacks deal an additional 1d8 slashing damage to plants.&nbsp; Additionally, wooden objects and structures take double damage from your attacks.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Javelin, Spear, or Trident</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pierce Pin</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: When making a throwing attack at a creature, the creature must make a Dexterity (Save) check of DC 8 + Proficiency Bonus + Dexterity Modifier or become </span><strong>grappled</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> by the attack as it pierces them.&nbsp; The grapple can be removed as a minor action, but the creature starts </span><strong>bleeding</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> if they do.</span></p><br /><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Water Weapon</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Attack and damage rolls are not negatively affected by being used in or under water.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Mace or Flail</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Internal Injury:</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> When you attack a </span><strong>prone</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> creature, it takes an extra 1d6 bludgeoning damage and it must make a Constitution (Save) check of DC 8 + your attack modifier.&nbsp; On failure, the creature takes 1d6 extra chaos damage at the beginning of its next turn.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Morning Star</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Aerate</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: When you land an attack, the target must make a Constitution (Save) check of DC 8 + your attack modifier.&nbsp; On failure, the creature starts </span><strong>bleeding</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> 2 Hit Points each turn.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pickaxe</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pierce</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: When targeting creatures with natural armor or wearing armor, add an amount equal to your proficiency bonus to attack rolls and damage rolls.&nbsp; This bonus is added after normal proficiency bonuses are added.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Pike</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Hold Position</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: While in Self-Defense, you can use your reaction to make an opportunity attack on a creature that moves into or within your attack range.&nbsp; If the attack hits, you regain your reaction and Hold Position ends.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Quarterstaff</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sweep the Leg</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: You add your proficiency bonus to Strength (Athletics) rolls as part of the Trip action.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rapier</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Have At Thee!:</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> If you use a desperate action before your first turn in combat, you can both move and make attack action.&nbsp; The first attack made this way deals 3d4 extra piercing damage.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p><br /><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lunge:</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> You can add 5ft of range to one attack per turn.</span></p><br /><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Feint Retreat</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: You can disengage as a non-action after landing an attack on a target.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Scythe or Sickle</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Reap</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: Once per turn, during your attack action, if a creature other than your target is within reach of you and within 5ft of your target, then you can make an attack against that target as well.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Shortsword, Midsword, Greatsword, or Scimitar</span></p></td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Lock Weapons: When you miss with a melee weapon attack against a creature of equal size, you can lock weapons with that target.&nbsp; While your weapons are locked, you have +1 AC against attacks from the target and the target provokes an opportunity attack from you if it uses its action to do anything other than attack you on its turn.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The weapon lock ends once either creature makes a weapon attack or leaves melee range.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Sling or Slingshot</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Cluster Shot</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: In place of an attack, you can attack a single target twice at disadvantage.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Unarmed</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Environmental Takedown</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: When you succeed on a </span><strong>shove</strong><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> action, pick one structure or other creature within 5ft of you to shove the creature into.&nbsp; Depending on the target, you get one of the following results:&nbsp;</span></p><ul><li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Structure: You smash the creature into a wall, large object, or structure.&nbsp; The creature takes bludgeoning damage equal to your unarmed attack damage.&nbsp; The structure takes equal damage.</span></li><li style=\"font-weight: 400;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Creature: You grab and slam one creature into another, giving both creatures bludgeoning damage equal to your Strength Modifier.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td>&nbsp;</td><td><p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Whip or Chain Whip</span></p></td><td><p><em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Seize</span></em><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">: You can attempt to grapple targets in place of your opportunity attack.&nbsp; Grapples made in this way add your proficiency bonus to the result of the grapple check, on top of any Strength (Athletics) bonus.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "novice"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "D5L8X9UJQABN9SJA", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Brand-Builder", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Brand Loyalty</em></p><p>Instead of 1 minute, you now keep your current heat for 1 hour of not gaining heat.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Dramatic Entrance</em></p><p>When you roll initiative, your current heat increases by half of your maximum heat.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Pressure to Perform</em></p><p>When making a skill check, you can add +1 to your roll for every 4 heat you spend, up to +5.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "C3FOXDT9CHAKP733", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Crowd-Worker", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Work the Crowd</em></p><p>As a minor action, if at least 1 non-combatant that you can see is watching you fight, you can play to the crowd to gain heat equal to your Presence (Perform) modifier, minimum of 1.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>This is for You</em></p><p>If at least 1 non-combatant that you can see is watching you fight, you can dedicate your next attack.&nbsp; If this attack kills or knocks a creature @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9KB959MRZ0H4IT4C]{Unconscious}, you automatically use &ldquo;Work the Crowd&rdquo; as a non-action.&nbsp; If you do, you can spend your heat to regain Hit Points.&nbsp; For every 1 heat you spend, you gain 1 Hit Point to a maximum of 20.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;If the attack fails to knock the creature @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9KB959MRZ0H4IT4C]{Unconscious}, you cannot use &ldquo;This is for You&rdquo; again for the next 1 minute.&nbsp; If the attack misses, you lose 10 heat.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "FBB0R61OTQY8CJ45", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Gladiatorial Role", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Gladiators fall into specific roles based on their external image that defines how they perform in different environments.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When you get this ability, pick one of the following Gladiatorial Roles and gain all of the abilities listed with it.</p><p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You can change your Gladiatorial Role, but it takes some time to change your public image and get used to the role.&nbsp; You can do so by practicing your new image as a <em>Long Rest Action</em>.&nbsp; When you do, you lose access to the traits of your previous Gladiatorial Role and may choose another one.&nbsp; If you change Gladiatorial Roles within 1 month of the last change, then you can only gain half heat for 1 week following.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Gladiatorial Roles</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Gladiatorial Role: Face</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Some gladiators, known as faces, find their fighting energy from being the protagonist.&nbsp; Be it as a hero, a helper, or an entertainer, faces feed off of encouragement.&nbsp; The more that onlookers want faces to win, the more that faces push themselves up to and past their limits.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>You present yourself as an underdog in combat, or otherwise the crowd-demanded overdog, and aim to get people rooting for you to win.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Role Ability: Heat Gain</strong></p><p>When you start your turn, you gain heat equal to half the total damage that you took since the start of your last turn, up to your <strong>Maximum Heat</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><br /><p><strong>Role Ability: Underdog</strong></p><p>As a minor action, you can gain 1 temporary Hit Point for every 2 heat you spend.&nbsp; This changes to 2 temporary Hit Points for every 2 heat if you have a <strong>Condition</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Gladiatorial Role: Heel</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Heels, unlike faces, get their fighting energy from being an antagonist.&nbsp; Jeers drive heels just as much as cheers.&nbsp; No matter the situation, the energy of the room as a whole encourages heels to outshine enemies and allies alike.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>You present yourself as an overdog, antagonist, or menace on the battlefield, aiming for some sort of crowd reaction to drive you past your limits.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Role Ability: Heat Gain</strong></p><p>When you end your turn, you gain heat equal to half the total damage that you dealt this turn, up to your <strong>Maximum Heat</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><br /><p><strong>Role Ability: Overdog</strong></p><p>Before you make an attack, for every 5 heat you spend, you deal an additional 1d4 damage.&nbsp; This changes to 1d8 additional damage if the target creature has a <strong>Condition</strong>.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "726QUN63DM3JKKPN", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Heat", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>&ldquo;Heat&rdquo; is the cumulative energy that you gain from being witnessed in battle.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>You gain heat based on your Gladiatorial Role, up to your <strong>Maximum Heat</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Your heat depletes after 1 minute of not gaining heat.</p><p><br /><em>Maximum Heat</em> = 5 times half of your overall level.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "SEFGUA8X0TGZPWT2", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Performer", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain proficiency in Presence (Perform) if you were not already proficient in it.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "0KTT2Y0R01HSBXB3", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance: Andabata", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/eyes/humanoid-single-blind.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><i>Requirement:</i> The @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ADW4EH0NKRDCRCA4]{Blinded} condition or some other total lack of sight.</p><hr><p>In some lands, public executions are handled as entertainment, with blindfolded fighting being a popular form.  These prisoners were expected to die in the arena, but some of them continued to survive.  These gladiators had found the secrets to blind fighting, extending their livelihoods in the process.  This strategy did not go unnoticed as word spread of its success, entering more traditional battlefields in the process.  <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Andabata Stance is entering a different state of mind.  Instead of fighting for a crowd, those trained in the stance are often after the thrill of fighting blind itself and the risks that brings.  <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;By widening your stance and obscuring or closing your eyes if not already @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ADW4EH0NKRDCRCA4]{Blinded}, you open your mind and begin to listen.  You feel for vibrations in the ground and sounds in the air, bringing your weapons in close to your body both for defense and to keep from losing them.  With some practice, as your mind clears and focuses, you find yourself able to 'see' without eyes and fight without sight.</p><hr><u>Pros</u><p><b>Blind Thrill</b><ul><li>You gain +10 heat at the beginning of your turn.</li><li>You gain an additional +10 heat if you were attacked this turn, whether it hits or misses.</li></ul><b>Heat Vision</b><ul><li>At the beginning of your turn, you can spend heat to give yourself blindsight as a non-action.  For every 5 heat you spend you have 5ft extra of blindsight until the beginning of your next turn.</li></ul><b>Sight Through Sound</b><ul><li>You have advantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on hearing.</li></ul></p><hr><u>Cons</u><p><b>Blind</b><ul><li>Excluding blindsight given by Heat Vision, you are @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ADW4EH0NKRDCRCA4]{Blinded}.</li></ul><b>Blind Ignorance</b><ul><li>You can only gain heat from the Blind Thrill ability.</li></ul></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "stance"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "2PGSXJZ46F6EQFIM", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance: Last Stance", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/death/skull-energy-light-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><i>Requirement:</i> When your Hit Points hit 0, if you are not killed outright then you can enter this stance as a non-action.</p><hr><p>Last stance is a special fighting stance that Gladiators can only enter under certain conditions and as a last resort.  <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Gladiators in last stance defy their failing bodies, staying up through force of will and the pressure alone.  They push their bodies past their limits, staying up at the cost of being fully conscious.</p><hr><u>Pros</u><p><b>Not Dead Yet</b><ul><li>When you enter this stance, you gain temporary Hit Points equal to your current heat, minimum of 1, and you remain conscious.</li></ul><b>Overdrive</b><ul><li>When you enter this stance, after gaining your temporary Hit Points, your heat is completely restored.</li></ul></p><hr><u>Cons</u><p><b>Practically Unconscious</b><ul><li>You automatically fail all Intelligence and Wisdom checks, and cannot speak intelligible words.</li></ul><b>Borrowed Time</b><ul><li>You automatically exit this stance by falling @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9KB959MRZ0H4IT4C]{Unconscious}, being healed, or being killed.  Otherwise the stance lasts 1 minute.</li></ul><b>Beyond Your Limits</b><ul><li>When you exit this stance, you take 1 point of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ERBR3AG01H4N1L91]{Exhaustion}.</li></ul><b>Bedrest</b><ul><li>You cannot enter this stance again until after a long rest.</li></ul></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "stance"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "HBZQK9WH0Z4JGM8L", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance: Scissor", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/trades/scissors-tailor-barber.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><i>Requirement:</i> Two slashing weapons.</p><hr><p>Turning your blades sideways and placing them across each other with the blades on the inside, resembling giant scissors.  You tilt your blades upward and bring them to your chest, ready to sever any part that falls between your blades by quickly yanking your blades in opposite directions.</p><hr><u>Pros</u><p><b>Disarm</b><ul><li>If a creature misses you with a melee weapon attack while you are in Self-Defense (or when not in Self-Defense at the cost of 5 heat), you can attempt to disarm the creature as a reaction (or as a non-action at the cost of 8 heat).  When you start the attempt, you make a contested attack roll using both you and the creature's current weapon.  If you succeed and the weapon can be disarmed; the creature's melee weapon is dropped in a direction of your choice within 5ft of the creature.</li></ul><b>Dis-Arm</b><ul><li>When your attack brings a humanoid's Hit Points to 0, you can spend 5 heat to instantly sever one of its limbs, giving the target a single failed Death Throw.  Doing so completely restores your heat.</li></ul></p><hr><u>Cons</u><p><b>Loose Grip</b><ul><li>Being hit by a melee weapon causes you to make a Dexterity (Save) check of DC equal to the attacking creature's Strength Attribute.  On failure, you drop one of your weapons.</li></ul></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "stance"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "CO89TKPTR5S0E00L", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance: Wrestling", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/environment/creatures/cephalopod-octopus-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><i>Requirement:</i> Unarmed, an unarmed weapon, or improvised weapons.</p><hr><p>When death is not the intent, wrestling is a common alternative form of strength-based entertainment.  The simplest form of wrestling is to grapple and pin the another creature, a talent which wrestlers have honed through years of practice.  While variations on these rules exist, the core concept remains, and wrestling gladiators want nothing more than to score an expert pin with an audience to cheer them on.</p><hr><u>Pros</u><p><b>Wrestle Spirit</b><ul><li>Before making a Strength (Athletics) roll related to grappling, you can add +1 to your roll for every 3 heat you spend to a maximum of +5. </li></ul><b>Pinning Hold</b><ul><li>If grappling a creature of equal or smaller size, you can attempt to grapple the creature again.  If you succeed, the creature is @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.EUHT2SOTAZ1MXEDB]{Pinned} by you.  If you fail, the creature remains @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.FGVFFYGPAFQGZ5RP]{Grappled}.  The pinned creature can attempt to break from this the same way as trying to break from being @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.FGVFFYGPAFQGZ5RP]{Grappled}.  However, upon succeeding, the creature is no longer @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.EUHT2SOTAZ1MXEDB]{Pinned} but remains @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.FGVFFYGPAFQGZ5RP]{Grappled}.</li></ul><b>Submission Hold</b><ul><li>If a creature @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.EUHT2SOTAZ1MXEDB]{Pinned} by you is unable to break out of being @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.EUHT2SOTAZ1MXEDB]{Pinned} after 3 attempts, the creature can no longer attempt to break from being @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.EUHT2SOTAZ1MXEDB]{Pinned} until it is attacked or you release it.</li><li>You gain +25 heat on the first turn that this happens.</li></ul></p><hr><u>Cons</u><p><b>Out Weight Classed</b><ul><li>You have disadvantage to grapple, or resist being @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.FGVFFYGPAFQGZ5RP]{Grappled} by, creatures that are at least 1 size larger than you.</li></ul></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "stance"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "18SU1HJZR146Z0UN", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fighting Stance: Gladiator", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/intimidation-impressing.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You learn 2 fighting stances from the following list.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When you can choose a new Fighting Stance as part of leveling up, you can choose from one of these Fighting Stances as well.<br><br><u><i>Fighting Stance List: Gladiator</i></u><br>@Compendium[undertaking.abilities.2PGSXJZ46F6EQFIM]{Andabata Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.18SU1HJZR146Z0UN]{Wrestling Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.HBZQK9WH0Z4JGM8L]{Last Stance}, @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.CO89TKPTR5S0E00L]{Scissor Stance}</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Fighter Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "SFNDJIWCV1ORHJTM", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Behavioral Experience", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have advantage on Presence (Insight) checks directed at members of your adopted race.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "IRC2M1N62DQTFVBH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Cultural Osmosis", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have advantage on Intelligence (Culture) checks related to your adopted race.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "5WJE2EYK49R6V2YW", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Early Bird", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/time/day-night-sunset-sunrise.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your first ability check after a long rest has advantage.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "JQVEQW294G49HFD8", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Farmer's Advantage", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/trades/farming-planet-bulb-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You add your proficiency twice to Wisdom (Nature) and Intelligence (Craft) checks in relation to farming or cooking if you are already proficient in either skill.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "1GWNHHDFP2B30LUH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Hard Sell", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/currency/coin-inset-crown-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Add your proficiency twice when using Wisdom (Insight), Presence (Persuasion), or Presence (Deception) checks in relation to bartering if you are already proficient in these skills.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "AGC864XWZMAXOUFX", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Night Owl", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/birds/raptor-owl-flying-moon.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You can sleep for 1 hour less than normal during a long rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "1G46RNQC5EFYGSXM", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Pet Pal", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/treasure/figurine-dog.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Add your proficiency twice to Wisdom (Instinct) checks toward domesticated beasts, such as pets and mounts, if you are already proficient in Wisdom (Instinct).", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "BX9VETXWGYCFYBBD", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Pocket Protector", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/theft-pickpocket-bribery-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You automatically have a +5 Awareness toward creatures using Dexterity (Sleight of Hand) on you.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "I7IHUKZI8GA0BZ11", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Blending In", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/chameleon-camouflage-green-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have advantage on Dexterity (Stealth) rolls when in dense foliage, smoke, or in dim or darker light.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "PK3LAXCYY6043RY5", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Elemental Spit", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/dragon-horned-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Unlike your brethren, you have to the ability to use a lesser version of the dragon&rsquo;s mighty breath weapon.&nbsp; Using an action, you can infuse your spit with elemental power and fire it at your foes.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;When you use this ability, select a single target within 30ft of you that you can see.&nbsp; Roll a ranged attack with proficiency.&nbsp; On a hit, the creature takes 2d6 damage.&nbsp; This damage increases to 3d6 at overall level 6, 4d6 at overall level 11, and 5d6 at overall level 16.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The type of damage dealt with this attack matches the element that you are resistant to with Draconic Resilience.&nbsp; You can use this ability a number of times equal to your proficiency modifier per short or long rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "action", "cost": 1, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": 30, "long": 30, "units": "ft"}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "rwak", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [["2d6", "varies"]], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}, "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "UVQHH4CUD3D9PVZR", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Fascinating Colors", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/buff-luck-fortune-rainbow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have advantage on Presence (Persuasion) and Presence (Deception) checks when trying to convince someone to seem less threatening.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "ZNZV2MPB10KLX45B", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Glide", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/biological/wing-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As an action, you can choose to enter a Glide while you are airborne that lasts until you land.  While gliding: <ul><li>You may choose how far you fall at the end of each round, to a minimum of 10 feet.  You do not fall on the turn that you enter Glide.  </li><li>You can only use your movement to descend.  </li><li>For every 5 feet you fall or descend while gliding, you can move 10 feet horizontally.  </li><li>If you land while gliding, you don't take fall damage.</li></ul></p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "8O5WZBNA6CHJTPSE", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Helping Hand", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/diplomacy-handshake-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You can use a minor action to give an ally advantage on the next attack roll that they make.  You must end your turn adjacent to the target to do this.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "2H84NPVAS7007JRB", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Lesser Flight", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/biological/wing-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have a pair of leathery dragon wings sprouting from your shoulder blades.  Your wings give you a flying speed of 30 feet.  This benefit works only in short bursts, however.  You fall if you end your turn in the air and nothing else is holding you aloft, such as Glide.  Between Limited Flight and Glide, your total horizontal movement each turn cannot exceed twice your flying speed.  You cannot fly in heavy armor.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "IX6N1K5PUGT3QCMV", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Sharp Claws", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/claws/claw-hooked-curved.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your claws are strong enough to do lethal damage.  They deals 1d4 slashing damage and are considered Finesse weapons.  You have proficiency for these natural weapons, and can use them to attack when you are holding nothing in them.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "1AW2E5YMMC1IGGP9", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Strength in Numbers", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/dragon-horned-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain a +1 to Wisdom (Save), Intelligence (Save), and Presence (Save) checks for each ally within 10 feet, excluding yourself in any form, that isn't @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.3CQC3JEY2C3Y721F]{Incapacitated}, up to a maximum of +3.  </p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "core"}, "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "XOU10R2EBHUGDPCQ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Tough Scales", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/reptiles/dragon-horned-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You have natural armor equal to 12 + your Dexterity Modifier while not wearing armor.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "activation": {"type": "", "cost": null, "condition": ""}, "duration": {"value": "", "units": ""}, "cover": null, "target": {"value": null, "width": null, "units": "", "type": ""}, "range": {"value": null, "long": null, "units": ""}, "uses": {"value": null, "max": "", "per": null, "recovery": ""}, "consume": {"type": "", "target": null, "amount": null}, "attribute": null, "actionType": "", "attackBonus": "", "chatFlavor": "", "critical": {"threshold": null, "damage": ""}, "damage": {"parts": [], "versatile": ""}, "formula": "", "save": {"attribute": "", "dc": null, "scaling": "spell"}, "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}, "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "6H6U8OS3L3B97ICX", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Enochian", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-runed-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You know the language of the ancient spellcasters, and can read magic runes. You can speak, read, and write enochian, though your writings contain no power on their own.</p><p>Magic runes are now readable by you. Most runes on enchanted objects tell you what magical effect they have, sometimes also revealing the creator of the enchantment. Others leave cryptic warnings behind. You have expertise in Intelligence (Arcana) checks to interpret how a magic item works if it is adorned in magic runes.</p><p>In addition, if you fulfill a vocal component of a spell by speaking in enochian, you gain the additional charge option:</p><ul><li>2 Mana: The spell no longer requires targets to hear or understand you, and the spell&rsquo;s damage is converted to Chaos damage as it scars reality.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "QEBX3GHOS7POI4FW", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Leylines", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-pentagon-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As a minor action, you trace a circle in the air around your feet, causing mystical and slightly glowing leylines to appear beneath you in a 5ft radius, lasting for 1 minute. Creating new leylines dissipates any previous leylines you created. Creatures within the leylines are made completely visible to all onlookers as if they could see them with true sight.</p><hr /><p><em>Requirement: </em>The <em>Slow Cast</em> ability.</p><hr /><p>While standing within your leylines, you have advantage on Concentration checks while Slow Casting, and Slow Casts can be completed with a minor action on your next turn, instead of an action.</p><hr /><p><em>Requirement: </em>The <em>Arcane Attraction</em> ability.</p><hr /><p>Leylines are also viable targets for Arcane Attraction, can be used as targets repeatedly, and can have resonance even while another resonance is active. When you first draw your leylines, they automatically resonate with you as described in the Arcane Attraction ability.</p><hr /><p><em>Requirement: </em>The <em>Up-Cast</em> ability.</p><hr /><p>While standing within your leylines, your charge limit is further increased by 1 mana.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "XF1V319XZ78D9JGL", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Resonant Attraction", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/energy-stream-link-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>By bending the subspace around a creature and yourself, you can stretch the space between you and them like a rubber band. Such that, when released, the space between you ripples, flinging you toward them.</p><p>As a minor action, you can apply a magical resonance between you and another creature. The tension threatens to release, pulling you to them in an instant; resisting the pull is easy, letting go is just as easy. Only one resonance can be active at a time.</p><p>As a reaction, you can stop resisting the pull to immediately and directly move toward the resonant target up to 30 feet, stopping harmlessly adjacent to it and ending the resonance. As space bends, moving in this way feels almost like standing still, not requiring movement or affecting any simultaneous actions. However, if there is a solid obstacle between you and the target when releasing the tension, you slam into it and take falling damage for how far you moved. If @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.FGVFFYGPAFQGZ5RP]{Grappled}&nbsp;or loosely bound, you take 5 chaos damage and get another (Save) check to escape. If otherwise bound, you just take the 5 chaos damage.</p><p>When you fall unconscious while this frequency is active, you are automatically pulled to the nearest resonant target.</p><p>Such a resonance can only be applied to each creature once per long rest, as the wrinkled space around a creature needs time to recover.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "URSPXLXX4T08D0SZ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Slow Cast", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/time/hourglass-brown-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Magi push their spellcasting to their limits. So long as they retain focus, their spells can shake the battlefield.</p><p>When you cast an instantaneous spell or a concentration spell that takes only 1 action to cast, you can extend the casting time to last through your next turn. When you do, you must take an action on your next turn to select the target and finish the casting or the spell fizzles. When you successfully cast a spell in this way, the spell&rsquo;s damage dice automatically roll their highest value.</p><p>You cannot take any actions or movement while casting a spell this way, or else break your concentration on the spell. If attacked during this time, you make concentration checks to try and keep the spell from failing. If you take a desperate action to cast the spell immediately, you take a point of @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.ERBR3AG01H4N1L91]{Exhaustion}.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "V674JRH1IOBW11BE", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Magus Spells", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/books/book-black-grey.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Wizards that specialize in becoming a Magus learn the following spells as Wizard spells once able to cast Wizard spells of the same spell level.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Magus Spells</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Able to Cast</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Spells</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1st Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-1.37VLMG8DVH1QVCYM]{Conduit Shock}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-1.93IZ61HQGJ91795Y]{Brittle Beam}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2nd Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.spells-level-2.HVOF7QNI17K2O6C1]{Snowslide}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.XPI8O47UKUK45ZRP]{Weight of the World}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3rd Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-3.7UWC00HNXCOL4GFI]{Fireball}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-3.Z373UKDNQ9VFAMQD]{Syzygy}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4th Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>Acidic Wave*</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5th Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>---</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>6th Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-6.GAC3VH4EZJOKZ8U0]{Ruin}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>7th Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-7.6YF5LESOLNIOTVM1]{Despair}</p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "L1GHFAREZ9DVXIW0", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Up-Cast", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/light/explosion-star-glow-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When casting a wizard spell, your charge limit is increased by 1 mana. For example, if 3rd level Wizard spells are the highest level you can cast, each time you cast a spell you can now spend up to 5 mana in total, instead of 4, by adding a charge option.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "3ZNUE5OBA4KUN184", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Armiger's Armory", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/strike-weapons-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain proficiency in one weapon of your choice and one of the following:</p><ul><li>One additional weapon of your choice</li><li>Light armor</li><li>Medium armor</li><li>Shields</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "29L79CWTS5SNA9ES", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Impossible Stance", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/maneuver-greatsword-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<hr/><p><em>Requirement: </em>The <em>Fighting Stance</em> ability from the <em>Fighter</em> class.</p><hr/><p>Using magic to sharpen your focus and give stability to your stances, you&rsquo;re able to make up for weaknesses that proficiency alone cannot solve.</p><p>When entering a Fighting Stance, you can choose to spend Mana equal to your proficiency bonus to ignore 1 of the Stance&rsquo;s Cons.</p><p>In addition, learn 1 Fighting Stance when you gain this ability.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Wizard Starter Abilities and the Fighting Stance ability from the Fighter class.", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "AJ29PDCH81I8B27R", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Spell Armor", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/defensive/shield-barrier-flaming-diamond-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You&rsquo;ve learned to always keep an imperceptible aura of magic around you, reinforcing your thoughts and body and merging with the energies of your mystic arts.</p><p>While conscious, you can add your Intelligence modifier to Concentration checks. In addition, you gain each of the following bonus abilities, so long as you meet their requirements:</p><br><hr/><p><em>Requirement: </em>The <em>Spellarm</em> ability.</p><hr/><p>While <em>Spellarm</em> is active, you are resistant to the spell&rsquo;s damage type(s) (Max of 2).</p><br><hr/><p><em>Requirement: </em>The <em>Sword and Sorcery</em> ability.</p><hr/><p>When you cast a cantrip with a casting time of 1 action, you can take the Self-Defense action as a minor action.</p><br><hr/><p><em>Requirement: </em>The <em>Impossible Stance </em>ability.</p><hr/><p>When you are knocked @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.RK3DF56CKMQUV6DM]{Prone}, you can make a Concentration check to attempt to remain in your Fighting Stance. On a success, you can remain in your stance if you stand up before the end of your next turn.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "M8U825D68XPJKC0Q", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Spellarm", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/strike-axe-energy-pink.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Magic is powerful, mystical, but often the hardest part about it is that it lacks form. Spells, especially powerful ones, often require some form of stability or backbone to act as a conduit. It&rsquo;s the same when it comes to combat. Mystics of eld have found great success in sustaining the effects of magic spells by wrapping them around themselves and their weapons, instead of around their enemies. A sharpened blade can take a life, but one imbued with magic can do even more.</p><p>You gain an additional charge option that can be applied to spells with an instantaneous duration:</p><ul><li>x2 Mana: You instead imbue the spell or cantrip into a weapon you are holding for the next 1 minute, until you lose concentration on it, or another creature takes possession of the weapon. <br />The first time that weapon or ammunition fired from it strikes a target each round, the following happens:</li><ul><li>The weapon&rsquo;s damage die is two sizes smaller.</li><li>The stored spell is cast on the target originating from the weapon.</li><li>The spell&rsquo;s first spell attack automatically hits.</li></ul></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "Y5PXHIVN1CM6H74J", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Mystic Armiger Spells", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/books/symbol-axe-gold-grey.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Wizards that specialize in becoming a Mystic Armiger learn the following spells as Wizard spells once able to cast Wizard spells of the same spell level.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Mystic Armiger Spells</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Able to Cast</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Spells</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Wizard Cantrips</p></td><td><p>Pick 2: @Compendium[undertaking.spells-cantrips.P8AYYAYOXXDCGM9B]{Brace for Impact}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-cantrips.MB7NWQ5H11LSIVV7]{Caustic Needle}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-cantrips.0JWJ9J7A2AMSNDK0]{Jolt}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1st Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>Pick 1: @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.7N5KBCOM40ZX65EO]{Arcane Arrows}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.5F78LN7YILWPNJL2]{Ethereal Mail}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2nd Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>Pick 2: @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.3BUFFKXCN0WVRIMP]{Barrier}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.LO6PLV28RA6CBCLU]{Burst Into Flames}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.MFJSEGIJAH0UIH47]{Identify}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3rd Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>Pick 1: @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.FZ8CHP8N6M0PGLI1]{Discombobulate}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-3.6GFN59MWTZPMBQ61]{Haste}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4th Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>Pick 1: @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-4.WJRECI4EKOPLMTCE]{Battle Cloaking}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-4.7H0M1UB9Z1ZVHSJ0]{Remove Arms}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5th Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>---</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>6th Level Wizard Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-6.3I736YDSAFN1B3E3]{Hundred Spear Assault}</p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "QI8Z7PCV0BBCVFXO", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Sword and Sorcery", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/blade-tip-energy-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you cast a cantrip with a casting time of 1 action, you can make a single weapon attack as a minor action. This attack does not add your attribute modifier to its damage.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "VG98NJ22142VHWO6", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Multiplicity", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/defensive/illusion-evasion-echo-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><em>Unlock: </em>When you reach 6th level overall you may take the ability below</p><p>One of the Ninja&rsquo;s greatest abilities is to create copies of themselves and employ them in combat or use them to aid in deceit.&nbsp; As an Action a Ninja may create a Copy of themselves in a space adjacent to them.&nbsp; It costs 1 Spirit per Copy made, and a ninja can make 1 Copy at 6th level and 2 Copies at 12th level.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Copies move when you do in the initiative order and their actions are controlled by you.&nbsp; On the first turn summoned, a Copy may only move or take an action.&nbsp; After the turn they were summoned, a Copy may make an action and a move action.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>A Copy has the following statistics:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Base stats, skills, and proficiencies are identical to yours</li><li>A Copy has no class features aside from Sneak Attack and any Ninja abilities you possess at time of creation, aside from Multiplicity.</li><ul><li>A Copy&rsquo;s Sneak Attack deals 2d6 damage.&nbsp; When you hit 12th level, it goes up to 3d6.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul><li>Hit Points equal to your overall character level + your proficiency bonus</li><li>They must spend Spirit to use Ninja abilities as the base class states</li><li>Spirit equal to half your proficiency bonus</li><li>They are wearing the same armor as you, and carry a copy of a single weapon on your person, but gain none of your other equipment.&nbsp; Any magical effects from your weapon or armor does not work for your Copy</li><li>A Copy gains the following abilities as well:&nbsp;</li><ul><li>Shared Mind: A Copy knows everything that its creator knows, including languages.&nbsp; As well, everything that a Copy senses is known to its creator, provided they are on the same plane, and even over great distances.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>Telepathic Bond: While a Copy is on the same plane as its creator, it can share what it senses with them and communicate telepathically.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li></ul><li>A Copy lasts for 1 minute after summoned before vanishing</li><li>Should their Hit Points drop to 0, or their Spirit drop to 0, a Copy and all equipment they were created with, vanishes</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "6th level overall, must have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "ILG1OGOCEP2L619C", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Mystic Seals", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-magenta.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Ninjas can evoke special mystic abilities through the use of Spirit and a combination of hand seals.&nbsp; You learn these Mystic Seals over time, receiving Detonate upon taking this ability, and the others you gain the other Ninja abilities as specified in their descriptions:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Detonate</strong></p><p>As a Minor Action you can spend 1 Spirit to imbue a piece of ammunition or a thrown weapon with the ability to explode on a successful strike, causing them to deal an extra 1d6 force damage to the target.&nbsp; This enhancement lasts until used or the end of your next turn.&nbsp; Whichever comes first.&nbsp; The thrown weapon or ammunition used is destroyed in the process.</p><p>Alternatively, you can instead spend 1 Spirit as part of your Attack Action and make a finesse unarmed attack against a target.&nbsp; On a success, the target takes 2d6 force damage from a small explosion originating at the point which you struck them, in addition to normal unarmed damage.&nbsp; Should you have the ability to make more than one attack a turn, this ability only takes up one.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Sudden Fog</strong></p><p><em>Unlock:</em> Received upon taking Run Like The Wind.</p><p>As an Action you can spend 1 Spirit to create a fog in your current space that has a 10 foot radius.&nbsp; The fog heavily obscures the area it covers and allows you to immediately make a Dexterity (Stealth) check after it is created.&nbsp; The fog lasts for 1 minute before dissipating.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Hide Below</strong></p><p><em>Unlock:</em> Received upon taking Shadow Walk.</p><p>This ability can be cast in two different ways:&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>As an Action: you can spend 1 Spirit to sink into the ground beneath you, provided its solid stone, dirt, or sand.&nbsp; The space you are sinking into must be large enough to fully contain your body.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>You are hidden beneath the ground giving you complete concealment.&nbsp; While hidden you have 0 speed, have disadvantage on Dexterity (Save) checks, and can take no action other than resurfacing as a minor action.&nbsp; You can still hear and discern through listening what is going on above you and can tell when a creature is within 10 feet of you.</p><p>After 1 minute of hiding in this way, you have the choice of spending 1 Spirit to stay hidden, or resurface as a minor action and take the rest of your turn.&nbsp; Should you have 0 Spirit at the start of your turn while this ability is active, you immediately resurface.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Should the space where you are hiding be destroyed, you surface immediately and are ejected 5 feet in a random direction.&nbsp; If not possible, you simply surface immediately.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>Taking 10 Minutes: to use this ability causes it to act as it is described above with a couple exceptions:</p><ul><li>You only have to spend 1 Spirit for the initial cast and for every 10 minutes you are hidden this way</li><li>You can hear up to 15 feet around you</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p><strong>Substitution</strong></p><p><em>Unlock:</em> Received upon taking Multiplicity.</p><p>As a reaction when you take damage, you can spend 1 Spirit to switch places with a Copy that you have created with Multiplicity.&nbsp; The Copy must be within 60 feet to do so, and it takes the damage instead of you.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "PLHRF3R67K6ELYGN", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Run Like The Wind", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/movement/feet-winged-boots-glowing-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>A Ninja must be ready to move through any terrain and cross any obstacle to accomplish their goals.&nbsp; With this ability you can walk across water as if it were solid ground, as long as you do not start or end your turn on or in the water.&nbsp; Should you end your turn over water, you may spend 1 Spirit to stay standing on its surface and continue walking across the water next turn.&nbsp; If you started in water, you may spend 1 Spirit to rise to its surface and walk across it.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, you may spend 1 Spirit on your turn to gain one of the following abilities until the start of your next turn.&nbsp; You may have more than one of these active at a time, but each one still costs 1 Spirit:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Walk across other liquids as if they were water, using the same rules stated above.</li><li>Walk along walls as though they were flat terrain.</li><li>Ignore rough terrain.</li><li>Run across a gap, chasm, etc.&nbsp; as long as you start and end your movement on solid ground.&nbsp; This kind of movement can only be made horizontally.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "1N6CJP6HAF725FR3", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Shadow Walk", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/mammals/wolf-shadow-black.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Shadows are your home and the terrain in which you excel the most.  While in shadows or moving while Stealthed your movement speed is doubled.  Additionally, while using the Hide action, Stealthed, or in shadows, others have disadvantage on Wisdom (Perception) checks to notice you.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "GQTOQHRNTQNSYXX6", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Spirit", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/nature/tree-spirit-glow-black-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Spirit energy is the inner power that a Ninja harnesses to perform great feats of supernatural power and evoke the elements in specific ways.&nbsp; A number of the Ninja&rsquo;s abilities rely on spending Spirit to make them happen.&nbsp; The amount of Spirit you have is equal to:&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><ul><li>4 + your proficiency bonus + either your Intelligence or Presence modifier (whichever is higher)</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><p>You regain all of your Spirit after a long rest, and a short rest restores an amount of Spirit equal to your proficiency bonus.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "JQ3I9PYSEKDJ5F06", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Way of the Ninja", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/weapons/swords/sword-katana.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain proficiency in Intelligence (Arcana) and either dagger, midsword, or throwing star.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "6HKS62RNGHEOJFHU", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Concurrency", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/time/hourglass-tilted-glowing-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When an ally takes their turn directly before you, or else you take your turn directly before an ally, you can spend a Reaction to instead share a turn.  On a shared turn, each creature's Actions, Minor Actions, Reactions, or Desperate Actions can be taken in any order between creatures who share a turn.  <br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;For each Growth Level, another ally with an adjacent turn can join the shared turn.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Order Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "YOHN2SD20CALZT81", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Act: Divine Average", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/social/trading-justice-scale-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p><p>You can spend @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Dice in the following ways:</p><ul><li><strong>Divine Average:</strong> Spend a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die before you roll a skill check or attack roll to automatically roll 10 instead. This does not count as an Eikonic Number.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Order Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "QRO01LDH2F2Y4XKO", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Divine Commandment", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/control/control-influence-crown-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As a Minor Action, you can proclaim 1 <strong>Divine Commandment</strong> from the <em>Divine Commandment Table</em> below.&nbsp; For the next 1 minute, you radiate a 60ft radius sphere of divine aura that binds all creatures within by said <strong>Divine Commandment</strong>, so long as they have an intelligence of 6 or higher.&nbsp; Creatures are only bound by the commandment while in the radius, and they innately know when they are under the effects of the commandment, even if they did not hear the pronouncement.&nbsp; All creatures within the radius understand the conditions of the commandment, even if they share no languages with you.&nbsp; During the duration, you can use a Minor Action to proclaim a new Divine Commandment, but the duration does not reset.&nbsp; You can use this ability once per Rest and you gain an additional usage of this ability at each Growth Level.</p><p>During the duration, if you see a creature break the commandment, then as a Reaction you can announce the offender and either make one weapon attack or a melee spell attack that deals 1d10 + your Wisdom Modifier Radiant Damage on hit.  If the target would be out of range, a holy weapon duplicating your own briefly conjures adjacent to the target to attack instead.  Either way, this attack has advantage and ignores cover.</p><p>If you break your own Divine Commandment, you lose 1 @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die.&nbsp; If you have no @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Dice, the Divine Commandment ends and you cannot make the same Divine Commandment until your next Rest.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Divine Commandments Table</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Commandments</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Law Breaking</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>&ldquo;Be silent.&rdquo;</p></td><td><p>Talking; using spells with a Vocal component or listed audio effect.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>&ldquo;Cease flight.&rdquo;</p></td><td><p>Starting flying or ending your turn while flying.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>&ldquo;Conserve energy.&rdquo;</p></td><td><p>Charging a spell.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>&ldquo;Do not bear false witness.&rdquo;</p></td><td><p>Saying something this Cleric sincerely and totally believes to be false.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>&ldquo;No loitering.&rdquo;</p></td><td><p>Not using movement speed before the end of your turn.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>&ldquo;No running.&rdquo;</p></td><td><p>Dash Action.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>&ldquo;No violence.&rdquo;</p></td><td><p>Dealing damage.</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>&ldquo;Remain orderly.&rdquo;</p></td><td><p>Take a Desperate Action.&nbsp;</p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Order Dominion", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "4298EW53PUXRT405", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Number of Order", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/cog-orange-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain a new Eikonic Number which serves as your <strong>Eikonic Number of Order</strong> (see the &ldquo;Eikonic Numbers&rdquo; Cleric Starter Ability for details).</p><p>You also gain access to the following <strong>Mantras</strong>, which can only be assigned to your <strong>Eikonic Number of Order</strong>:</p><ul><li><strong>Justice Never Rests:</strong> You gain an extra Reaction until the start of your next turn.</li><li><strong>Lawful:</strong> You immediately know either:</li><ul><li>An important law, natural or legal, of the area you are in.</li><li>Someone who has broken the law in the last 24 hours within 1 mile of you.</li></ul><li><strong>Oath to Order</strong>: Move an event or creature&rsquo;s turn up or back in the Turn Order by 1 slot. This can only affect the same target once per turn.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "NU56ZP100JW4HO08", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Law Abiding", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/cog-orange-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Once per long rest, when you enter into an agreement that would reasonably be beneficial for at least the other creature, you are bound by your word.  You gain a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die upon completing the agreement without breaking the terms.  You lose a @Compendium[undertaking.abilities.65D4NMYRBMKHW59K]{&#x1F56F; Faith} Die if you break the terms of the agreement.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "HAM7R26DCCISOZJH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Refined Magicks", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/cog-orange-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain proficiency in Intelligence (Arcana) if you were not already proficient in it.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "NON1FUV6X5DENLGZ", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Order Dominion Spells", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/cog-orange-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Clerics of the Order Dominion learn the following spells when able to cast Cleric spells of the same spell level.&nbsp; These spells are always prepared and don&rsquo;t count against your prepared spell amount.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>Dominion spells are considered Cleric spells when learned this way.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Order Dominion Spells</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Able to Cast</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Spells</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1st Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.MRQUPL1D078DKFR2]{No Reproach}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-1.3XZ089KFBQMQUFK5]{Tunnel Vision}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2nd Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.RSOH8YFIDRSE3ZCL]{Repress Emotions}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-2.YCQC074MGCT6R2NY]{Ultimatum}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3rd Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-3.XD6W9NSEKZ48HGCD]{Dispel Magic}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-3.Z373UKDNQ9VFAMQD]{Syzygy}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>4th Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-4.XJ75LFYCND9DK4GP]{Banish}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-4.7H0M1UB9Z1ZVHSJ0]{Remove Arms}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5th Level Cleric Spells</p></td><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-5.N2ZSVB7D1W068EWZ]{Ashame}, @Compendium[undertaking.spells-level-5.J9QLMOBH6NXLN5OQ]{Telepathic Network}</p></td></tr></tbody></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "3K61WI41NGFFQZL2", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Cheap Shot", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-white-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As your Sneak Attack grows more deadly, you can do more than just deal damage. Before rolling Sneak Attack damage dice on an attack, you can forgo rolling some of the Sneak Attack damage dice to add an effect to one target hit by the attack instead. If you have enough Sneak Attack dice to spend, you can apply multiple effects as part of one Sneak Attack.</p><p>Unless listed as indefinite, Cheap Shot conditions last until the end of the affected target&rsquo;s next turn.</p><p>The conditions that you can apply, and the damage from your Sneak Attack needed to use it is shown below:</p><p><br /><br /></p><p><em>Cheap Shot Table</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Sneak Attack Dice Cost</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Applied Condition</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1d6</p></td><td><p>The target gains 2 stacks of indefinite @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3d6</p></td><td><p>The target becomes @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9X088PM7H5U2S1HQ]{Sickened}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5d6</p></td><td><p>The target must make a Constitution (Save) check or become @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.PEDR1J13VZXKUF3C]{Stunned}</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>7d6</p></td><td><p>The target must make a Constitution (Save) check or become @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.OBTES08D2XC130IG]{Paralyzed}</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The DC for this ability is:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>8 + your proficiency modifier + half of the number of your Sneak Attack dice (minimum 1)</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Rogue", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "XIJRUICHXRXLH3K6", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Desperate Quickness", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/movement/arrow-upward-yellow.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your quick reflexes and thinking allow you to push yourself to the extreme and move faster within a split second than others.&nbsp; The respective bonuses granted are doubled when using a desperate action to:</p><ul><li>Shove or move a target</li><li>Dodge an AoE with a Dexterity (Save) check</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Must have a Rogue Adept Ability", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "MK99LKGD8IHJ48QD", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Evasive", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/fire/explosion-embers-evade-silhouette.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Your agility and alertness has made it hard to hit you.&nbsp; Should an attacker that you can see successfully hit you with an attack, you can use a reaction to add +2 to your AC.&nbsp; If this causes the attack to miss, you take no damage and can immediately Disengage and move up to half your speed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Additionally, when you are subjected to a Dexterity (Save) check made to take half damage from an effect, on a success you instead take no damage.&nbsp; On a failure, you still only take half damage.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "adept"}, "requirements": "6th level overall and 3rd level Rogue", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "X90JYLUREXENZDQC", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Exploit", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-blood-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you fight, you fight to win by taking advantage of weaknesses in your opponents and exploiting them to the fullest. And you are exceptionally good with your tool of the trade in doing this.</p><p>Choose a single weapon that you are proficient with. That weapon now scores a critical hit on a roll of 19 and 20.</p><p>Additionally, you deal extra damage to creatures that are suffering from conditions. On a successful hit against a creature that is suffering from a condition, you add your proficiency bonus to damage on the attack; if that hit is a Sneak Attack, then you also add your Dexterity Modifier again.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "adept"}, "requirements": "6th level overall and 3rd level Rogue", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "T4YIHUPQPW9YAAV6", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Multi-Talented", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-merchant-scribe.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Rogues are exceptionally talented folks, seeking expertise in many different skills so that they can be prepared for any situation that arises.&nbsp; Upon taking this ability, you choose two skill or tool proficiencies that you have, and for that skill your proficiency bonus is doubled for any skill check you make regarding it.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><p><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You pick another skill or tool proficiency to apply this bonus to when you reach 5th level overall, 11th level overall while at Adept Rogue, and at 17th level overall while at Expert Rogue.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "novice"}, "requirements": "Must have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "5H1YLH3E742DLXDK", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "One Step Ahead", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/movement/feet-winged-boots-brown.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>A Rogue has many ways of getting out of harm&rsquo;s way.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p><ul><li>At the end of each of your turns in combat as a non-action, you can attempt to Hide (should circumstances allow you to perform the Hide action) but at a disadvantage.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>You can spend a minor action to Dash while stealthed.&nbsp;&nbsp;</li><li>You can use a reaction to Disengage if an enemy fails to hit you with a melee attack on their turn and immediately take a 5 foot step away from them.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "novice"}, "requirements": "Must have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "JXY8GNKY37UR93L6", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Sneak Attack", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/melee/strike-dagger-white-orange.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Through skill and cunning you know exactly where to strike someone to hurt them best and how to do it with subtlety. Starting at 1st level, once per turn you can deal extra damage to a single creature as a Sneak Attack under certain conditions.</p><p>Sneak Attack can only be applied to Dexterity weapon attacks or attacks with the Light weapon property, and cannot be applied while attacking at disadvantage. In addition, you must either:</p><ul><li>Have advantage on the attack.</li><li>Have a non-@Compendium[undertaking.conditions.3CQC3JEY2C3Y721F]{Incapacitated}<br />&nbsp;ally, or otherwise an enemy to the target, within 5 feet of the target.</li></ul><p>If the attack is a Critical Hit, ignore all previous requirements.</p><p>The amount of damage that a Sneak Attack deals increases as you gain levels in the Rogue class, as shown in the table below:</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><em>Sneak Attack Table</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Rogue Level</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Sneak Attack Damage</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1-2</p></td><td><p>1d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>3-4</p></td><td><p>2d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>5-6</p></td><td><p>3d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>7-8</p></td><td><p>4d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>9-10</p></td><td><p>5d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>11-12</p></td><td><p>6d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>13-14</p></td><td><p>7d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>15-16</p></td><td><p>8d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>17</p></td><td><p>9d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>18</p></td><td><p>10d6</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><br /><br /></p><p><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The Sneak Attack level is equal to your Rogue level, plus &frac12; of every non-Rogue level, rounded down. For example, a level 7 Wizard / Level 4 Rogue would have a Sneak Attack Level of 7, and could thus deal 4d6 Sneak Attack damage.</p><p><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;You can do more than just deal damage with a Sneak Attack, however.&nbsp; As your Sneak Attack grows more deadly, you gain the ability to apply conditions to target&rsquo;s on a successful hit from your Sneak Attack.&nbsp; When you make a Sneak Attack you can declare a condition that you have access to through this ability, to inflict on the target.&nbsp; Should you successfully hit, the target takes damage and must make a Constitution (Save) check (listed below), and if it fails, now has that condition.</p><p><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;The conditions that you can apply, and the damage from your Sneak Attack needed to use it is shown below:</p><p><br /><br /></p><p><em>Sneak Attack Effects Table</em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Condition</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Sneak Attack Damage Needed</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}</p></td><td><p>1d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.conditions.9X088PM7H5U2S1HQ]{Sickened}</p></td><td><p>3d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.conditions.PEDR1J13VZXKUF3C]{Stunned}</p></td><td><p>5d6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>@Compendium[undertaking.conditions.OBTES08D2XC130IG]{Paralyzed}</p></td><td><p>7d6</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The DC for this ability is:&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>8 + your proficiency modifier + half the number of die on your Sneak Attack (minimum 1)&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;With the exception of <strong>@Compendium[undertaking.conditions.R54LQEKSDXNQ3N75]{Bleeding}, </strong>a condition affecting a creature from this ability lasts until the end of their next turn.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Rogue", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "1P8DJ5ZSPPJRMLWH", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Speak in Code", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/documents/document-symbol-triangle-pink.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Either during your formal training, from a run in with another Rogue, or some other happenstance of the profession, you have in some way, shape, or form, come to understand the Code of Thieves'.  It is a specific way of speaking that hides messages in plain speech through shifts in utterance, jargon, and turns of phrases.  Additionally, there is also a short hand and special symbolic signage that is used to help relay simplistic information, such as locations, territory, sanctuary, and marks for instance.<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Only others that know the Code of Thieves' can understand it, and speaking it takes four times longer to get an idea across than it would simply saying it in layman's terms.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Rogue", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "A3GDM85RSHS80N3U", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Sunlight Sensitivity", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/perception/eye-tendrils-web-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>While in sunlight, you have disadvantage on attack rolls, as well as on Wisdom (Perception) checks that rely on sight.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "race", "subtype": "branch"}}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "0YK75ZQYDRVHEP50", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Five-Finger Discount", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/bones/bones-hand-grey.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>A thief&rsquo;s hands are trained in delicate procedures, a natural quickness that allows for sneaky operations. As thieves act throughout the day, their mental and physical acuity is drained, until they inevitably botch an attempt. Thieves sometimes call these &ldquo;Thief Fingers&rdquo; or simply Fingers (with a capital F), referring to how many more tricks the thief can pull off before failing.</p><p>You have 5 &ldquo;Fingers&rdquo; (regardless of how many <em>fingers</em> you have) which represent the deftness of your most thieving faculties. They can be spent to take certain Thief actions.</p><p>Fingers are regained at the end of a rest.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "EE5KJBK43K69MTT5", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Kleptomania", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/equipment/hand/glove-simple-leather-brown-blue.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>When you thieve, you feel a rush of adrenaline&mdash;a high off of the excitement of repossession, regardless of the worth of the item itself. This feeling keeps you moving, and keeps you on your toes as you make your escape.</p><p>After successfully stealing something, you can:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Disengage as a non-action.</li><li>Until the start of your next turn, move through the space of other creatures at half speed, should you have been blocked by them instead.</li><li>For the next minute, gain temporary hit points equal to your proficiency bonus at the start of your turn.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "POBHBOBIFM6899DA", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Master Thief", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/commodities/currency/coin-embossed-ruby-gold.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Thieves are skilled in the art of the transition. The transition of one&rsquo;s attention from here to there. The transition of items of theirs to yours. The transition of here and gone.</p><p>As a master thief, you gain the following Thief abilities:</p><p><strong>Steal (1 Finger)</strong></p><p>As an action, you swipe a random item from a creature within 5 feet of you. Roll a Dexterity (Sleight of Hand) check, with advantage if they don&rsquo;t know that you&rsquo;re there, and with disadvantage if they are actively hostile toward or suspicious of you.</p><p>Regardless of the result, you steal one item from the target as determined by the GM, with higher results meaning you swipe larger or rarer items from the target&rsquo;s possession. With this ability, you cannot steal any items they are being directly held or clutched, or that are not easily detachable, nor items they do not possess.</p><p>If the creature has no separate items or equipment in their possession, or if it would better match the Steal roll&rsquo;s result, you instead break, tear, or cut off a piece of the creature to take as an item. As a result, the creature&rsquo;s natural weapons are reduced by 1 die size. This can only be done once per creature, and lasts until their next long rest.</p><p><strong>Swipe (3 Fingers)</strong></p><p>As an action, you attempt to take a held or clutched weapon or item from a creature within 5 feet of you. Roll a contested Dexterity (Sleight of Hand) check against the target. If you succeed, you take the item from their hand, and are proficient in the weapon for the next 1 minute.</p><p>If the stolen item is a weapon, you can immediately make an attack against the target using this weapon.</p><p><strong>Mug</strong></p><p>If you hit a creature as part of the Attack Action, you can use either Steal or Swipe against that creature as a Minor Action before the end of your turn.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "NFT3RSXOWDP7SS1X", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Spell Thief", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/unholy/hand-marked-pink.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>While most thieves steal or borrow possessions, some thieves specialize in the thievery of the arcane. It turns out, many of the principles are the same: lower a target&rsquo;s defenses, move in, and take what you want. However, instead of a pocket, you&rsquo;re reaching into their soul or otherwise.</p><p>While harder to fence, spell thieves are particularly adept in combat scenarios and at taking on spellcasters&mdash;many of them are spellcasters themselves. Indeed, the art of spell thievery is sometimes cultivated in military and mercenary bands for its anti-magical talents.</p><p>As a spell thief, you gain the following Thief abilities:</p><p><strong>Strip Down (2 Fingers)</strong></p><p>As a minor action, steal a non-instantaneous magical or spell effect off of another creature that is within 5ft of you and place it on yourself. If the spell effect required concentration, you now maintain that concentration for the remainder of its duration. An effect that lasts longer than 24 hours cannot be stolen.</p><p><strong>Lost Marbles (2 Fingers)</strong></p><p>Replacing 3d6 Sneak Attack, you can steal 1 Mana from a creature, turning into a small marble-sized mote of solid Mana.</p><p>Mana Motes can be absorbed as a Minor Action to gain 1 Mana. If not used within 1 hour, the Mana Mote dissipates.</p><p><strong>Spell Steal (2 Fingers)&nbsp;</strong></p><p>As a reaction to a cantrip being cast within 30 ft of you, you can spend 2 Fingers to attempt to steal their knowledge of the cantrip. The caster must succeed on a Concentration check versus your Sneak Attack DC or else the spell fails, you temporarily learn the cantrip, and they are unable to cast the cantrip again until their next long rest. On a success, you fail to steal the cantrip and they cast the spell normally.</p><p>When you learn a cantrip from this ability, choose Intelligence, Wisdom, or Presence to be your spellcasting attribute for the cantrip. If the cantrip has verbal components, you must be able to hear the caster to learn it, likewise if it has somatic or material components you must be able to see the caster to learn it.</p><p>You forget the cantrip learned from this ability when you finish a rest or learn a different cantrip using this ability. However, each time you finish a rest, you can choose not to forget your current cantrip at the cost of not regaining one of your expended Fingers.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "26JCNSTKXQ52FM2O", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Sticky Fingers", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/webs/web-spider-caught-hand-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>You gain proficiency in two of the following:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Dexterity (Sleight of Hand)</li><li>Dexterity (Stealth)</li><li>Presence (Deception)</li><li>Thievery Trade</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "UQMIR0G36A5Y12FE", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Street Rat", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/creatures/mammals/rodent-rat-diseaed-gray.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>To become a thief, one must have a certain level of determination and focus to allow delicate acts quickly and with a high variety of unpredictability. One must also know every trick in the book to get themselves out of danger and into your pockets.</p><p>As a street rat, you gain the following Thief abilities:</p><p><strong>Thief&rsquo;s Focus (1 Finger)</strong></p><p>When making a Sleight of Hand or Stealth check, before knowing the result, you can spend 1 Finger to increase the result by +5.</p><p><strong>Catch!</strong></p><p>You can pass an item no heavier than 6 lbs to another creature up to 20 ft away. So long as the creature can see you, is willing, and is capable, they automatically catch the item.</p><p><strong>Quaff</strong></p><p>You can drink any potion or potion-sized drink as a Minor Action instead of an Action.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "subclass"}, "requirements": "Must have the Rogue Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "I3ZGJ4PULFJFHGD3", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Book of Spells", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/skills/trades/academics-book-study-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>An essential tool for many Wizards is their spellbook. It is where all their most important research regarding the nature of magic and the universe around them is written down.</p><p>When first taking this Wizard Ability, the Wizard hits a breakthrough, and casts a one-time ritual spell to create the spellbook from scratch. As part of this process, they choose the design of the spellbook&rsquo;s cover and binding. When the book is created, it contains your arcane scrawlings on all of the spells you know, and you add to this spellbook as you learn new ones.</p><p><strong>Your Spellbook</strong></p><p>Any spellbook you create can function as an arcane focus for you, and so long as you channel your spells into it as part of a long rest all of the spells you know are automatically prepared instead of having to choose.</p><p>In addition, if you are in possession of any spell scrolls or spellpages, you can tuck them between the pages of your spellbook to temporarily add a number of spells up to your proficiency bonus to your spellbook. These spells must be of a level which you can cast, and they remain prepared until you channel again. Tucked spell scrolls are not destroyed when their spell is cast in this way.</p><p>Each spellbook is inherently linked to the wizard who wrote it. As such, Wizards cannot prepare or cast spells from another wizard&rsquo;s spellbook. Should you find yourself in possession of another wizard&rsquo;s spellbook, you may be able to make use of some of its contents as described in the <em>Salvaging a Spellbook</em> section.</p><p><strong>Treatise</strong></p><p>When you select this ability, you also gain a loose spellpage containing one Wizard spell you don&rsquo;t already know that is of a level you could learn.</p><p><strong>Replacing a Spellbook</strong></p><p>Because of their mystical construction, spellbooks are highly resistant to most natural elements; they do not easily burn, soak, or tear, and any such damage is magically mended the next time it is channeled, if the damage is not too severe. However, it is not unheard of for a Wizard&rsquo;s spellbook to be rendered unrepairable in extreme circumstances. When a spellbook is destroyed, any loose spell scrolls or spellpages tucked inside are destroyed with it.</p><p>Should a Wizard lose their spellbook and have to write a new one, they can do so as a <em>Long Rest Action</em> with a new and empty spellbook or any suitable medium&mdash;though any improvised option will be less durable than a proper spellbook. During this process, they can copy down all of the spells they know. Spells that you don&rsquo;t know but had temporarily prepared due to spell scrolls or spellpages that were tucked into your old spellbook are not recovered.</p><p><strong>Salvaging a Spellbook</strong></p><p>Because of the arcane bond between a wizard and their spellbook, as well as the inscrutable proprietary scrawlings made by the wizard for each spell, other wizards cannot cast spells from another wizard&rsquo;s spellbook.</p><p>Instead, wizards can perform a 1 minute ritual to carefully separate one spell&rsquo;s page from a spellbook, turning it into a discrete spellpage for use in tucking into your spellbook, as described above. Unfortunately, this separation process destroys the spellbook in the process.</p><p><strong>Sharing Spells</strong></p><p>While many wizards closely guard their accumulated arcane secrets for fear of what could come about were they to fall into the wrong hands, collaboration between wizards can lead to even greater knowledge. As a <em>Rest Action</em>, you can copy one Wizard spell you know onto a discrete spellpage, should you have one in your possession.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "novice"}, "requirements": "Must have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "L4TCBW3PWUZVSULN", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Efforless Cantrips", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/fire/flame-burning-hand-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Whenever you Charge a cantrip, reduce its total mana cost by 1 (minimum 0). Use the un-reduced mana cost when checking if it satisfies the limit for how much mana you can spend on a single spell.</p><p>In addition, when a creature triggers an attack of opportunity from you, you can use your reaction to cast a cantrip at the creature instead of making an opportunity attack. The cantrip must have a casting time of 1 action or less and must only target that creature.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "adept"}, "requirements": "6th level overall and 3rd level Wizard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "ZG3FXZY4IZX4LH6N", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Meditative Rest", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/survival/bedroll-blue-red.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Whenever a Wizard takes a rest, they can also spend Rest Dice to regain Mana instead of hit points. Do not add your Constitution modifier to rest dice spent in this way.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "given"}, "requirements": "Must have a Wizard Adept Ability", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "SHD2ABFLNZ9CNNII", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "School of Study", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/books/book-stack.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>As you get your feet under you as a Wizard, you naturally gravitate toward certain schools of magic, specializing in the spells and capabilities innate to that school. Pick one school of magic to specialize in:</p><ul><li><em>Abjuration</em></li><li><em>Conjuration</em></li><li><em>Divination</em></li><li><em>Evocation</em></li><li><em>Illusion</em></li><li><em><em>Mesmerization</em></em></li><li><em>Necromancy</em></li><li><em>Transmutation </em></li></ul><p>Each time you cast a spell from your chosen school of magic you gain the following bonuses:&nbsp;</p><ul><li>Gain a +1 bonus on one of the spell&rsquo;s spell attack modifiers.</li><li>Gain a +1 bonus on one of the spell save DCs for that spell.</li></ul><p>In addition, based on your chosen school, you learn Spell Charges that can be used with any spell, and gain a unique bonus to all spells that you cast with that school. These Spell School Bonuses can be found beneath this section.</p><p><em>Learning New Schools of Study:</em> You become an expert in 1 additional School of Study at each of the following:</p><ul><li>The first of either Spellcaster level 8 or Wizard level 6.</li><li>The first of either Spellcaster level 16 or Wizard level 12.</li><li>Wizard level 18.</li></ul><h3>Spell School Bonuses</h3><p><strong>Abjuration</strong></p><p>The following Spell Charges are now options for any reasonably applicable spell:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: Spells that have area effects can be manipulated to cause some or all creatures to not be affected by the spell.</li></ul><p>When you cast an Abjuration spell, you can choose to apply this additional effect:</p><ul><li>Gain temporary hit points equal to twice the mana spent on the spell, adding on top of any you already have. Afterward, if the spell targets a creature other than you, you can also transfer any number of your temporary hit points to them.</li></ul><p><strong>Conjuration</strong></p><p>The following Spell Charges are now options for any reasonably applicable spell:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: You briefly conjure a lesser spirit that will deliver this spell instead of you. <br />The lesser spirit can be conjured anywhere you can see within 60 ft of you. However, if the spell has a range of touch, the Mana cost increases by 1, and spirit can only be conjured within 30 ft of you. <br />The spirit dissipates after the spell is cast, when struck mid-casting, or when the spellcasting is otherwise prevented. <br />If the spirit is dissipated before it can cast the spell, then you can cast it from yourself instead and may select a different target if the original is no longer targetable.&nbsp;</li></ul><p>When you cast a Conjuration spell, you can choose to apply this additional effect:</p><ul><li>Conjure a <em>Conjured Wisp</em> at the target point of the spell. The wisp has no senses, but it is under your complete control, acting on your turn.</li></ul><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Conjured Wisp</strong></p><p><em>Tiny Elemental</em></p><p>Armor Class: 10</p><p>Hit Points: 1</p><p>Writer: Hudson Bielstein</p><p>Speed: Float 30 ft.</p><p>Challenge: 0 (0 XP)</p><p>Str - 1 (-5) | Dex - 1 (-5) | Con - 1 (-5)</p><p>Int - 1 (-5) | Wis 1 (-5) | Pres - 1 (-5)</p><p>Senses: None</p><p>Skills: --</p><p>Languages: --</p><p><em>Wisp</em>: The wisp glows just enough to be seen in the dark. It cannot use the assist action.</p><p><em>Wisp of Burden: </em>A wisp can surround and magically carry an object weighing no more than 2 lbs.&nbsp;</p><p><em>Disperse</em>: When the wisp moves into another creature, it can dissipate and deal 1 psychic damage as a non-action.</p><p><em>Fleeting</em>: Conjured wisps dissipate automatically after 1 hour.</p><p>Actions in Combat</p><p>Flare: As an action, the wisp can dissipate to cast 15ft of bright light and an additional 15ft of dim light from where it dissipated. This light lasts until the would-be start of its next turn.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Divination</strong></p><p>The following Spell Charges are now options for any reasonably applicable spell:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: Choose one creature affected by the spell. Increase or decrease the result of the chosen creature&rsquo;s next roll by 2.</li></ul><p>When you cast a Divination spell, you can choose to apply this additional effect:</p><ul><li>If this spell costs mana, choose a creature you can see, roll a d20, look at it, and set the result aside. Within the next 10 minutes, the next d20 roll made by that creature is replaced by the result you rolled instead. You cannot use this ability again until the d20 you set aside is used or the 10 minutes are up, whichever comes first.</li></ul><p><strong>Mesmerization</strong></p><p>The following Spell Charges are now options for any reasonably applicable spell:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: You do not provoke attacks of opportunity from the targets of this spell this turn.</li><li>1 Mana: Choose one creature affected by the spell. The target must make a Wisdom (Save) check. On a failure, the creature&rsquo;s movement speeds become 0. <br />Flying creatures remain aloft or glide to the nearest stable footing if they are capable of doing so.</li><li>1 Mana: Choose one creature affected by the spell. The target must make a Wisdom (Save) check. On a failure, you can force them to move their full speed toward or away from you at the start of their next turn, taking the safest route to do so.</li></ul><p>When you cast a Mesmerization spell, you can choose to apply these additional effects:</p><ul><li>If this spell does not charm the target, the creature must make a Wisdom (Save) check against your spell save DC or become @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed}&nbsp;for 1 minute. The charm ends early if you or one of your allies attacks the creature. When the spell ends, the creature knows it was charmed by you.</li><li>While a creature is @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed}&nbsp;by you, it cannot knowingly harm creatures you designate.</li></ul><p><strong>Evocation</strong></p><p>The following Spell Charges are now options for any reasonably applicable spell:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: One of the spell&rsquo;s damage rolls deals 5 additional damage of the same damage type.</li></ul><p>When you cast an Evocation spell, you can choose to apply this additional effect:</p><ul><li>You can reroll 1s on any of your dice rolled as part of this spell, except for 1s rolled on d20s.</li></ul><p><strong>Illusion</strong></p><p>The following Spell Charges are now options for any reasonably applicable spell:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: When you cast a spell, you can make it appear like it came from a creature adjacent to you instead.  If the spell would apply a mental effect like @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.KJXJ0T5RPNC51N4V]{Charmed}&nbsp;or @Compendium[undertaking.conditions.UK95BQ45TGSD5Q3V]{Frightened}, then these apply as if the adjacent creature cast the spell instead.</li></ul><p>When you cast an Illusion spell, you can choose to apply this additional effect:</p><ul><li>You create an illusory duplicate of yourself for 1 minute. The duplicate is controlled by you, acting on your turn with the same movement speed. When you speak or make any other sound (such as clapping) then your duplicate emits the same audio. For the duration, both you and the duplicate appear illusory, being slightly blurry and translucent so as to appear indistinguishable. <br />When one of you is attacked or otherwise touched, struck, or injured, flip a coin. If heads, that figure was you and the event is carried out like normal. As a result, your duplicate dissipates. If tails, that figure was your illusory duplicate. Any interaction passes through it, causing it to dissipate. <br />If one of you would take an action that would affect the surroundings, the other you dissipates, revealing the acting figure to be the real one.<br />If your illusory double dissipates from time running out, choose which one was yourself the whole time.<br />The double does not confuse creatures that rely on senses other than sight or sound.</li></ul><p><strong>Necromancy</strong></p><p>The following Spell Charges are now options for any reasonably applicable spell:</p><ul><li>2 Mana: When you cast a spell that requires a Constitution (Save) check, you can attempt to drain the vigor from one target. If the chosen creature fails the spell&rsquo;s first Constitution (Save) check, you can choose to sap either its Strength or Dexterity. Until the target takes a long rest, that attribute of theirs is decreased by 1. Until you take a long rest, that attribute of yours is increased by 1. <br />Keep track of your original attribute scores and update your modifier accordingly.</li></ul><p>When you cast a Necromancy spell, <em>or</em> when an undead creature under your control hits a creature with an attack, you can choose to apply this additional effect:</p><ul><li>As a reaction, you can use one 1 of your rest dice to deal additional necrotic damage. Roll the chosen rest die and deal necrotic damage to the target equal to the result.  Additionally, you can cause one creature within 10ft of the target to restore an equal amount of hit points.</li></ul><p><strong>Transmutation</strong></p><p>The following Spell Charges are now options for any reasonably applicable spell:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: You can enchant a non-living item or 5ft space with the effects of this spell. After completing the casting time of the spell, it is applied to the chosen target within the spell&rsquo;s range, but delays the spell's effect to trigger when the item or surface is touched by a creature. As part of the casting, you can designate up to 3 creatures to be unable to trigger the effect. The target is not highlighted by this enchantment, so creatures without some ability to detect magic would not see what was enchanted, even if they saw you casting the enchantment.<br />When the enchantment is triggered, the triggering creature becomes the target of the spell's effects. When triggered by a creature unawares, the spell&rsquo;s first spell attack has advantage to hit, and the target has disadvantage against its first spell save.<br />If not triggered within 10 minutes of being placed, the enchantment dissipates.</li></ul><p>When you cast a Transmutation spell, you can choose to apply this additional effect:</p><ul><li>The duration of this spell is doubled, if its duration is not instantaneous.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "novice"}, "requirements": "Must have the Wizard Starter Abilities", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "RFBX1FZ2ALJA5G3Z", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Spellcasting (Wizard)", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/symbols/rune-sigil-black-pink.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Wizards use arcane means to formulate spells that bend the world to their will. What is deemed mythical or impossible to many, Wizards view as elementary calculations of science. Mathematics, physics, alchemy, magic&mdash;all are equally capable of using and breaking down the laws of the universe to allow feats once thought impossible.</p><p><strong>Cantrips</strong></p><p>Upon gaining your 1st level of Wizard, you know three Cantrips from the Wizard&rsquo;s spell list. You gain an additional Cantrip when you first reach Adept Wizard, and then another at Expert Wizard.</p><p><strong>Spells at 1st Level</strong></p><p>At 1st level, your mind bursts with magical inspiration, quickly discovering and memorizing six 1st level spells of your choice from the Wizard&rsquo;s spell list to permanently know.</p><p><strong>Mana</strong></p><p>Wizards, like all spellcasters, expend Mana to cast spells (expanded upon in the Mana section of <strong>&ldquo;Chapter 9: Magic &amp; Spellcasting&rdquo;</strong>). They regain all spent Mana after a long rest, and half of their maximum Mana on a short rest.</p><p><strong>Arcane Spellcasting Focus</strong></p><p>You may use an arcane focus, a specialized item used to channel and cast spells, as a spellcasting focus for casting your Wizard spells.</p><p>While in the Wizard&rsquo;s possession, a spellcasting focus allows spells to be cast without most material components. Material components that have a cost or are said to be used up by the spell cannot be replaced using an arcane focus.</p><p><strong>Preparing and Casting Spells</strong></p><p>Wizards, unlike other spellcasters, must use an arcane focus, a specialized item used for casting, in order to prepare or cast their complex Wizard spells.</p><p>A Wizard channels a series of spells into their spellcasting focus from their known spells. These become the list of spells available to them while wielding it, and they lose access to casting those spells while the focus is not in their possession. They do this by, each long rest, selecting a number of known Wizard spells to prepare equal to:</p><ul><li>Your Wizard level + your Intelligence modifier. (Minimum of 1)</li></ul><p>This channeling is personal and lasts until they channel again&mdash;no two spellcasting foci can store your prepared spells at once, and other Wizards cannot cast your spells using your arcane focus.</p><p>The spells the Wizard prepares are available to be cast until they decide to prepare another spell in its place. A Wizard can change the spells they have prepared at the end of a long rest.</p><p>Note: To figure out how many and what spells you know, reference the <strong>Spells at 1st Level</strong> above this section, and if needed, the <strong>Learning Spells at Higher Levels </strong>section below this one.</p><p><strong>Spellcasting Ability</strong></p><p>Being that you obtain your magic ability through intense study and memorization, Intelligence is the spellcasting ability for a Wizard. Meaning that your Intelligence modifier comes into play when setting the DC for your Wizard spells and when making an attack with one.</p><ul><li><em>Spell Save DC: </em>8 + your proficiency bonus + your Intelligence modifier&nbsp;</li></ul><ul><li><em>Spell Attack Modifier: </em>your proficiency bonus + your Intelligence modifier</li></ul><p><strong>Ritual Casting</strong></p><p>You can cast a Wizard spell as a Ritual if that spell has the Ritual tag and you know the spell. You do not need to have the spell prepared when casting a spell this way.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Wizard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "RGKNFQH7M4AJXSXV", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Wizard Spells", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/sundries/scrolls/scroll-runed-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>1st level Wizards get access to Wizard Magic, which consists of 1st through 7th level spells.  However, you do not have access to all of them right away.  These spell levels become accessible as follows:</p><p><i>Wizard Spell Levels</i></p><table><tr><th>Spell Level</th><th>Unlock Requirements</th></tr><tr><td>Level 1 Spells</td><td>1st Level Wizard.</td></tr><tr><td>Level 2 Spells</td><td>2nd Level Wizard;<br>3rd Level Overall.</td></tr><tr><td>Level 3 Spells</td><td>3rd Level Wizard;<br>5th Level Overall<br>(At least 4 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 4 Spells</td><td>4th Level Wizard;<br>7th Level Overall<br>(At least 6 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 5 Spells</td><td>5th Level Wizard;<br>9th Level Overall<br>(At least 8 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 6 Spells</td><td>6th Level Wizard;<br>11th Level Overall<br>(At least 10 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr><tr><td>Level 7 Spells</td><td>7th Level Wizard;<br>13th Level Overall<br>(At least 12 of these levels must be in Spellcaster classes).</td></tr></table>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "starter"}, "requirements": "Wizard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "U2NS38QP7TBT6SMG", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Visceral Casting", "type": "ability", "img": "icons/magic/unholy/strike-body-life-soul-green.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>What&rsquo;s difficult to learn through teaching or reading, is that as your experience grows, sometimes the best casts come from more than just impeccable pronunciation and precision wrist flicks. With a bit of emotion, instinct, and brute forcing, you&rsquo;ve found the theoretical limits of spells to be more flexible than they appear.</p><p>When you cast a spell, you have access to additional charge options depending on its spell components.</p><p>If the spell has a <strong>Somatic</strong> component, you can choose to meet that component with at least two hands to gain access to the following charge options:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: Increase one of the spell&rsquo;s damage amounts by either 2d6 or 1d12.</li><li>1 Mana: Extend the range of a touch spell by 5ft.</li><li>X Mana: Target two creatures within 5ft of each other instead of one if it is a single-target spell. The charge cost is equal to half of the spell&rsquo;s mana cost.</li></ul><p>If the spell has a <strong>Verbal</strong> component, you can choose to meet that component by shouting its incantation to gain access to the following charge options:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: Extend the range of a non-touch spell by 15ft.</li><li>2 Mana: Increase the spell save DC by 2.</li><li>2 Mana: Expand the spell&rsquo;s areas of effect, increasing the dimensions of each shape by 5ft.</li></ul><p>If the spell has a <strong>Material</strong> component that you are meeting using a spellcasting focus, but you supply the spell with material components anyway, then you gain access to the following charge option:</p><ul><li>0 Mana: Every listed material component is consumed by the casting. As a result, reduce the casting time of the spell:&nbsp;</li><ul><li>If the casting time is greater than 1 minute, reduce it by 1 minute.</li><li>If the casting time is 1 minute or less but greater than an Action, cast it as an Action.</li><li>If the casting time is an Action, cast it as a Minor Action.</li><li>If the casting time is a Minor Action, cast it as a Reaction.</li></ul><li>X Mana: If the casting time is 1 hour or more, reduce the casting time by half. The mana cost is equal to each hour removed from the spell, minimum of 1.</li></ul><p>If the spell has either a Verbal or Somatic component, you gain access to the following charge option:</p><ul><li>1 Mana: The spell no longer requires a Verbal component. However, spells that amplify a verbal component still require your voice.</li><li>1 Mana: The spell no longer requires a Somatic component. Spells with a range of touch can be applied to creatures within 5ft without having to touch them.</li></ul>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "type": {"value": "class", "subtype": "adept"}, "requirements": "6th level overall and 3rd level Wizard", "recharge": {"value": null, "charged": false}}, "folder": null, "_id": "DNKUZOHBFP8JQ80N", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
